2884/* Subroutine of push_inner_scope. */
2885
2886static void
2887push_inner_scope_r (tree outer, tree inner)
2888{
2889 tree prev;
2890
2891 if (outer == inner
2892 || (TREE_CODE (inner) != NAMESPACE_DECL && !CLASS_TYPE_P (inner)))
2893 return;
2894
2895 prev = CP_DECL_CONTEXT (TREE_CODE (inner) == NAMESPACE_DECL ? inner : TYPE_NAME (inner));
2896 if (outer != prev)
2897 push_inner_scope_r (outer, prev);
2898 if (TREE_CODE (inner) == NAMESPACE_DECL)
2899 {
2900 cp_binding_level *save_template_parm = 0;
2901 /* Temporary take out template parameter scopes. They are saved
2902 in reversed order in save_template_parm. */
2903 while (current_binding_level->kind == sk_template_parms)
2904 {
2905 cp_binding_level *b = current_binding_level;
2906 current_binding_level = b->level_chain;
2907 b->level_chain = save_template_parm;
2908 save_template_parm = b;
2909 }
2910
2911 resume_scope (NAMESPACE_LEVEL (inner));
2912 current_namespace = inner;
2913
2914 /* Restore template parameter scopes. */
2915 while (save_template_parm)
2916 {
2917 cp_binding_level *b = save_template_parm;
2918 save_template_parm = b->level_chain;
2919 b->level_chain = current_binding_level;
2920 current_binding_level = b;
2921 }
2922 }
2923 else
2924 pushclass (inner);
2925}
2926
2927/* Enter the scope INNER from current scope. INNER must be a scope
2928 nested inside current scope. This works with both name lookup and
2929 pushing name into scope. In case a template parameter scope is present,
2930 namespace is pushed under the template parameter scope according to
2931 name lookup rule in 14.6.1/6.
2932
2933 Return the former current scope suitable for pop_inner_scope. */
2934
2935tree
2936push_inner_scope (tree inner)
2937{
2938 tree outer = current_scope ();
2939 if (!outer)
2940 outer = current_namespace;
2941
2942 push_inner_scope_r (outer, inner);
2943 return outer;
2944}
2945
2946/* Exit the current scope INNER back to scope OUTER. */
2947
2948void
2949pop_inner_scope (tree outer, tree inner)
2950{
2951 if (outer == inner
2952 || (TREE_CODE (inner) != NAMESPACE_DECL && !CLASS_TYPE_P (inner)))
2953 return;
2954
2955 while (outer != inner)
2956 {
2957 if (TREE_CODE (inner) == NAMESPACE_DECL)
2958 {
2959 cp_binding_level *save_template_parm = 0;
2960 /* Temporary take out template parameter scopes. They are saved
2961 in reversed order in save_template_parm. */
2962 while (current_binding_level->kind == sk_template_parms)
2963 {
2964 cp_binding_level *b = current_binding_level;
2965 current_binding_level = b->level_chain;
2966 b->level_chain = save_template_parm;
2967 save_template_parm = b;
2968 }
2969
2970 pop_namespace ();
2971
2972 /* Restore template parameter scopes. */
2973 while (save_template_parm)
2974 {
2975 cp_binding_level *b = save_template_parm;
2976 save_template_parm = b->level_chain;
2977 b->level_chain = current_binding_level;
2978 current_binding_level = b;
2979 }
2980 }
2981 else
2982 popclass ();
2983
2984 inner = CP_DECL_CONTEXT (TREE_CODE (inner) == NAMESPACE_DECL ? inner : TYPE_NAME (inner));
2985 }
2986}

3036/* Set INHERITED_VALUE_BINDING_P on BINDING to true or false, as
3037 appropriate. DECL is the value to which a name has just been
3038 bound. CLASS_TYPE is the class in which the lookup occurred. */
3039
3040static void
3041set_inherited_value_binding_p (cxx_binding *binding, tree decl,
3042 tree class_type)
3043{

3045 {
3046 tree context;
3047
3048 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == OVERLOAD)
3049 context = ovl_scope (decl);
3050 else
3051 {
3052 gcc_assert (DECL_P (decl));
3053 context = context_for_name_lookup (decl);
3054 }
3055
3056 if (is_properly_derived_from (class_type, context))
3057 INHERITED_VALUE_BINDING_P (binding) = 1;
3058 else
3059 INHERITED_VALUE_BINDING_P (binding) = 0;
3060 }
3061 else if (binding->value == decl)
3062 /* We only encounter a TREE_LIST when there is an ambiguity in the
3063 base classes. Such an ambiguity can be overridden by a

3065 INHERITED_VALUE_BINDING_P (binding) = 1;
3066 else
3067 INHERITED_VALUE_BINDING_P (binding) = 0;

3070/* Make the declaration of X appear in CLASS scope. */
3071
3072bool
3073pushdecl_class_level (tree x)
3074{
3075 tree name;
3076 bool is_valid = true;
3077 bool subtime;
3078
3079 /* Do nothing if we're adding to an outer lambda closure type,
3080 outer_binding will add it later if it's needed. */
3081 if (current_class_type != class_binding_level->this_entity)
3082 return true;
3083
3084 subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
3085 /* Get the name of X. */
3086 if (TREE_CODE (x) == OVERLOAD)
3087 name = DECL_NAME (get_first_fn (x));
3088 else
3089 name = DECL_NAME (x);
3090
3091 if (name)
3092 {
3093 is_valid = push_class_level_binding (name, x);
3094 if (TREE_CODE (x) == TYPE_DECL)
3095 set_identifier_type_value (name, x);
3096 }
3097 else if (ANON_AGGR_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (x)))
3098 {
3099 /* If X is an anonymous aggregate, all of its members are
3100 treated as if they were members of the class containing the
3101 aggregate, for naming purposes. */
3102 tree f;
3103
3104 for (f = TYPE_FIELDS (TREE_TYPE (x)); f; f = DECL_CHAIN (f))
3105 {
3106 location_t save_location = input_location;
3107 input_location = DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (f);
3108 if (!pushdecl_class_level (f))
3109 is_valid = false;
3110 input_location = save_location;
3111 }
3112 }
3113 timevar_cond_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP, subtime);
3114 return is_valid;
3115}

3117/* Return the BINDING (if any) for NAME in SCOPE, which is a class
3118 scope. If the value returned is non-NULL, and the PREVIOUS field
3119 is not set, callers must set the PREVIOUS field explicitly. */
3120
3121static cxx_binding *
3122get_class_binding (tree name, cp_binding_level *scope)
3123{
3124 tree class_type;
3125 tree type_binding;
3126 tree value_binding;
3127 cxx_binding *binding;
3128
3129 class_type = scope->this_entity;
3130
3131 /* Get the type binding. */
3132 type_binding = lookup_member (class_type, name,
3133 /*protect=*/2, /*want_type=*/true,
3134 tf_warning_or_error);
3135 /* Get the value binding. */
3136 value_binding = lookup_member (class_type, name,
3137 /*protect=*/2, /*want_type=*/false,
3138 tf_warning_or_error);
3139
3140 if (value_binding
3141 && (TREE_CODE (value_binding) == TYPE_DECL
3142 || DECL_CLASS_TEMPLATE_P (value_binding)
3143 || (TREE_CODE (value_binding) == TREE_LIST
3144 && TREE_TYPE (value_binding) == error_mark_node
3145 && (TREE_CODE (TREE_VALUE (value_binding))
3146 == TYPE_DECL))))
3147 /* We found a type binding, even when looking for a non-type
3148 binding. This means that we already processed this binding
3149 above. */
3150 ;
3151 else if (value_binding)
3152 {
3153 if (TREE_CODE (value_binding) == TREE_LIST
3154 && TREE_TYPE (value_binding) == error_mark_node)
3155 /* NAME is ambiguous. */
3156 ;
3157 else if (BASELINK_P (value_binding))
3158 /* NAME is some overloaded functions. */
3159 value_binding = BASELINK_FUNCTIONS (value_binding);
3160 }
3161
3162 /* If we found either a type binding or a value binding, create a
3163 new binding object. */
3164 if (type_binding || value_binding)
3165 {
3166 binding = new_class_binding (name,
3167 value_binding,
3168 type_binding,
3169 scope);
3170 /* This is a class-scope binding, not a block-scope binding. */
3171 LOCAL_BINDING_P (binding) = 0;
3172 set_inherited_value_binding_p (binding, value_binding, class_type);
3173 }
3174 else
3175 binding = NULL;
3176
3177 return binding;
3178}

3180/* Make the declaration(s) of X appear in CLASS scope under the name
3181 NAME. Returns true if the binding is valid. */
3182
3183static bool
3184push_class_level_binding_1 (tree name, tree x)
3185{
3186 cxx_binding *binding;
3187 tree decl = x;
3188 bool ok;
3189
3190 /* The class_binding_level will be NULL if x is a template
3191 parameter name in a member template. */
3192 if (!class_binding_level)
3193 return true;
3194
3195 if (name == error_mark_node)
3196 return false;
3197
3198 /* Can happen for an erroneous declaration (c++/60384). */
3199 if (!identifier_p (name))
3200 {
3201 gcc_assert (errorcount || sorrycount);
3202 return false;
3203 }
3204
3205 /* Check for invalid member names. But don't worry about a default
3206 argument-scope lambda being pushed after the class is complete. */
3207 gcc_assert (TYPE_BEING_DEFINED (current_class_type)
3208 || LAMBDA_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (decl)));
3209 /* Check that we're pushing into the right binding level. */
3210 gcc_assert (current_class_type == class_binding_level->this_entity);
3211
3212 /* We could have been passed a tree list if this is an ambiguous
3213 declaration. If so, pull the declaration out because
3214 check_template_shadow will not handle a TREE_LIST. */
3215 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TREE_LIST
3216 && TREE_TYPE (decl) == error_mark_node)
3217 decl = TREE_VALUE (decl);
3218
3219 if (!check_template_shadow (decl))
3220 return false;
3221
3222 /* [class.mem]
3223
3224 If T is the name of a class, then each of the following shall
3225 have a name different from T:
3226
3227 -- every static data member of class T;
3228
3229 -- every member of class T that is itself a type;
3230
3231 -- every enumerator of every member of class T that is an
3232 enumerated type;
3233
3234 -- every member of every anonymous union that is a member of
3235 class T.
3236
3237 (Non-static data members were also forbidden to have the same
3238 name as T until TC1.) */
3239 if ((VAR_P (x)
3240 || TREE_CODE (x) == CONST_DECL
3241 || (TREE_CODE (x) == TYPE_DECL
3242 && !DECL_SELF_REFERENCE_P (x))
3243 /* A data member of an anonymous union. */
3244 || (TREE_CODE (x) == FIELD_DECL
3245 && DECL_CONTEXT (x) != current_class_type))
3246 && DECL_NAME (x) == constructor_name (current_class_type))
3247 {
3248 tree scope = context_for_name_lookup (x);
3249 if (TYPE_P (scope) && same_type_p (scope, current_class_type))
3250 {
3251 error ("%qD has the same name as the class in which it is "
3252 "declared",
3253 x);
3254 return false;
3255 }
3256 }
3257
3258 /* Get the current binding for NAME in this class, if any. */
3259 binding = IDENTIFIER_BINDING (name);
3260 if (!binding || binding->scope != class_binding_level)
3261 {
3262 binding = get_class_binding (name, class_binding_level);
3263 /* If a new binding was created, put it at the front of the
3264 IDENTIFIER_BINDING list. */
3265 if (binding)
3266 {
3267 binding->previous = IDENTIFIER_BINDING (name);
3268 IDENTIFIER_BINDING (name) = binding;
3269 }
3270 }
3271
3272 /* If there is already a binding, then we may need to update the
3273 current value. */
3274 if (binding && binding->value)
3275 {
3276 tree bval = binding->value;
3277 tree old_decl = NULL_TREE;
3278 tree target_decl = strip_using_decl (decl);
3279 tree target_bval = strip_using_decl (bval);
3280
3281 if (INHERITED_VALUE_BINDING_P (binding))
3282 {
3283 /* If the old binding was from a base class, and was for a
3284 tag name, slide it over to make room for the new binding.
3285 The old binding is still visible if explicitly qualified
3286 with a class-key. */
3287 if (TREE_CODE (target_bval) == TYPE_DECL
3288 && DECL_ARTIFICIAL (target_bval)
3289 && !(TREE_CODE (target_decl) == TYPE_DECL
3290 && DECL_ARTIFICIAL (target_decl)))
3291 {
3292 old_decl = binding->type;
3293 binding->type = bval;
3294 binding->value = NULL_TREE;
3295 INHERITED_VALUE_BINDING_P (binding) = 0;
3296 }
3297 else
3298 {
3299 old_decl = bval;
3300 /* Any inherited type declaration is hidden by the type
3301 declaration in the derived class. */
3302 if (TREE_CODE (target_decl) == TYPE_DECL
3303 && DECL_ARTIFICIAL (target_decl))
3304 binding->type = NULL_TREE;
3305 }
3306 }
3307 else if (TREE_CODE (target_decl) == OVERLOAD
3308 && is_overloaded_fn (target_bval))
3309 old_decl = bval;
3310 else if (TREE_CODE (decl) == USING_DECL
3311 && TREE_CODE (bval) == USING_DECL
3312 && same_type_p (USING_DECL_SCOPE (decl),
3313 USING_DECL_SCOPE (bval)))
3314 /* This is a using redeclaration that will be diagnosed later
3315 in supplement_binding */
3316 ;
3317 else if (TREE_CODE (decl) == USING_DECL
3318 && TREE_CODE (bval) == USING_DECL
3319 && DECL_DEPENDENT_P (decl)
3320 && DECL_DEPENDENT_P (bval))
3321 return true;
3322 else if (TREE_CODE (decl) == USING_DECL
3323 && is_overloaded_fn (target_bval))
3324 old_decl = bval;
3325 else if (TREE_CODE (bval) == USING_DECL
3326 && is_overloaded_fn (target_decl))
3327 return true;
3328
3329 if (old_decl && binding->scope == class_binding_level)
3330 {
3331 binding->value = x;
3332 /* It is always safe to clear INHERITED_VALUE_BINDING_P
3333 here. This function is only used to register bindings
3334 from with the class definition itself. */
3335 INHERITED_VALUE_BINDING_P (binding) = 0;
3336 return true;
3337 }
3338 }
3339
3340 /* Note that we declared this value so that we can issue an error if
3341 this is an invalid redeclaration of a name already used for some
3342 other purpose. */
3343 note_name_declared_in_class (name, decl);
3344
3345 /* If we didn't replace an existing binding, put the binding on the
3346 stack of bindings for the identifier, and update the shadowed
3347 list. */
3348 if (binding && binding->scope == class_binding_level)
3349 /* Supplement the existing binding. */
3350 ok = supplement_binding (binding, decl);
3351 else
3352 {
3353 /* Create a new binding. */
3354 push_binding (name, decl, class_binding_level);
3355 ok = true;
3356 }
3357
3358 return ok;
3359}

3373/* Process "using SCOPE::NAME" in a class scope. Return the
3374 USING_DECL created. */
3375
3376tree
3377do_class_using_decl (tree scope, tree name)
3378{
3379 /* The USING_DECL returned by this function. */
3380 tree value;
3381 /* The declaration (or declarations) name by this using
3382 declaration. NULL if we are in a template and cannot figure out
3383 what has been named. */
3384 tree decl;
3385 /* True if SCOPE is a dependent type. */
3386 bool scope_dependent_p;
3387 /* True if SCOPE::NAME is dependent. */
3388 bool name_dependent_p;
3389 /* True if any of the bases of CURRENT_CLASS_TYPE are dependent. */
3390 bool bases_dependent_p;
3391 tree binfo;
3392
3393 if (name == error_mark_node)
3394 return NULL_TREE;
3395
3396 if (!scope || !TYPE_P (scope))
3397 {
3398 error ("using-declaration for non-member at class scope");
3399 return NULL_TREE;
3400 }
3401
3402 /* Make sure the name is not invalid */
3403 if (TREE_CODE (name) == BIT_NOT_EXPR)
3404 {
3405 error ("%<%T::%D%> names destructor", scope, name);
3406 return NULL_TREE;
3407 }
3408 /* Using T::T declares inheriting ctors, even if T is a typedef. */
3409 if (MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (scope)
3410 && (name == TYPE_IDENTIFIER (scope)
3411 || constructor_name_p (name, scope)))
3412 {
3413 maybe_warn_cpp0x (CPP0X_INHERITING_CTORS);
3414 name = ctor_identifier;
3415 CLASSTYPE_NON_AGGREGATE (current_class_type) = true;
3416 }
3417 if (constructor_name_p (name, current_class_type))
3418 {
3419 error ("%<%T::%D%> names constructor in %qT",
3420 scope, name, current_class_type);
3421 return NULL_TREE;
3422 }
3423
3424 scope_dependent_p = dependent_scope_p (scope);
3425 name_dependent_p = (scope_dependent_p
3426 || (IDENTIFIER_TYPENAME_P (name)
3427 && dependent_type_p (TREE_TYPE (name))));
3428
3429 bases_dependent_p = any_dependent_bases_p ();
3430
3431 decl = NULL_TREE;
3432
3433 /* From [namespace.udecl]:
3434
3435 A using-declaration used as a member-declaration shall refer to a
3436 member of a base class of the class being defined.
3437
3438 In general, we cannot check this constraint in a template because
3439 we do not know the entire set of base classes of the current
3440 class type. Morover, if SCOPE is dependent, it might match a
3441 non-dependent base. */
3442
3443 if (!scope_dependent_p)
3444 {
3445 base_kind b_kind;
3446 binfo = lookup_base (current_class_type, scope, ba_any, &b_kind,
3447 tf_warning_or_error);
3448 if (b_kind < bk_proper_base)
3449 {
3450 if (!bases_dependent_p || b_kind == bk_same_type)
3451 {
3452 error_not_base_type (scope, current_class_type);
3453 return NULL_TREE;
3454 }
3455 }
3456 else if (name == ctor_identifier && !binfo_direct_p (binfo))
3457 {
3458 error ("cannot inherit constructors from indirect base %qT", scope);
3459 return NULL_TREE;
3460 }
3461 else if (!name_dependent_p)
3462 {
3463 decl = lookup_member (binfo, name, 0, false, tf_warning_or_error);
3464 if (!decl)
3465 {
3466 error ("no members matching %<%T::%D%> in %q#T", scope, name,
3467 scope);
3468 return NULL_TREE;
3469 }
3470 /* The binfo from which the functions came does not matter. */
3471 if (BASELINK_P (decl))
3472 decl = BASELINK_FUNCTIONS (decl);
3473 }
3474 }
3475
3476 value = build_lang_decl (USING_DECL, name, NULL_TREE);
3477 USING_DECL_DECLS (value) = decl;
3478 USING_DECL_SCOPE (value) = scope;
3479 DECL_DEPENDENT_P (value) = !decl;
3480
3481 return value;
3482}

3544
3545/* Set the context of a declaration to scope. Complain if we are not
3546 outside scope. */
3547
3548void
3549set_decl_namespace (tree decl, tree scope, bool friendp)
3550{
3551 tree old;
3552
3553 /* Get rid of namespace aliases. */
3554 scope = ORIGINAL_NAMESPACE (scope);
3555
3556 /* It is ok for friends to be qualified in parallel space. */
3557 if (!friendp && !is_ancestor (current_namespace, scope))
3558 error ("declaration of %qD not in a namespace surrounding %qD",
3559 decl, scope);
3560 DECL_CONTEXT (decl) = FROB_CONTEXT (scope);
3561
3562 /* Writing "int N::i" to declare a variable within "N" is invalid. */
3563 if (scope == current_namespace)
3564 {
3565 if (at_namespace_scope_p ())
3566 error ("explicit qualification in declaration of %qD",
3567 decl);
3568 return;
3569 }
3570
3571 /* See whether this has been declared in the namespace. */
3572 old = lookup_qualified_name (scope, DECL_NAME (decl), /*type*/false,
3573 /*complain*/true, /*hidden*/true);
3574 if (old == error_mark_node)
3575 /* No old declaration at all. */
3576 goto complain;
3577 /* If it's a TREE_LIST, the result of the lookup was ambiguous. */
3578 if (TREE_CODE (old) == TREE_LIST)
3579 {
3580 error ("reference to %qD is ambiguous", decl);
3581 print_candidates (old);
3582 return;
3583 }
3584 if (!is_overloaded_fn (decl))
3585 {
3586 /* We might have found OLD in an inline namespace inside SCOPE. */
3587 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TREE_CODE (old))
3588 DECL_CONTEXT (decl) = DECL_CONTEXT (old);
3589 /* Don't compare non-function decls with decls_match here, since
3590 it can't check for the correct constness at this
3591 point. pushdecl will find those errors later. */
3592 return;
3593 }
3594 /* Since decl is a function, old should contain a function decl. */
3595 if (!is_overloaded_fn (old))
3596 goto complain;
3597 /* We handle these in check_explicit_instantiation_namespace. */
3598 if (processing_explicit_instantiation)
3599 return;
3600 if (processing_template_decl || processing_specialization)
3601 /* We have not yet called push_template_decl to turn a
3602 FUNCTION_DECL into a TEMPLATE_DECL, so the declarations won't
3603 match. But, we'll check later, when we construct the
3604 template. */
3605 return;
3606 /* Instantiations or specializations of templates may be declared as
3607 friends in any namespace. */
3608 if (friendp && DECL_USE_TEMPLATE (decl))
3609 return;
3610 if (is_overloaded_fn (old))
3611 {
3612 tree found = NULL_TREE;
3613 tree elt = old;
3614 for (; elt; elt = OVL_NEXT (elt))
3615 {
3616 tree ofn = OVL_CURRENT (elt);
3617 /* Adjust DECL_CONTEXT first so decls_match will return true
3618 if DECL will match a declaration in an inline namespace. */
3619 DECL_CONTEXT (decl) = DECL_CONTEXT (ofn);
3620 if (decls_match (decl, ofn))
3621 {
3622 if (found && !decls_match (found, ofn))
3623 {
3624 DECL_CONTEXT (decl) = FROB_CONTEXT (scope);
3625 error ("reference to %qD is ambiguous", decl);
3626 print_candidates (old);
3627 return;
3628 }
3629 found = ofn;
3630 }
3631 }
3632 if (found)
3633 {
3634 if (!is_associated_namespace (scope, CP_DECL_CONTEXT (found)))
3635 goto complain;
3636 if (DECL_HIDDEN_FRIEND_P (found))
3637 {
3638 pedwarn (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), 0,
3639 "%qD has not been declared within %D", decl, scope);
3640 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (found), "only here as a friend");
3641 }
3642 DECL_CONTEXT (decl) = DECL_CONTEXT (found);
3643 return;
3644 }
3645 }
3646 else
3647 {
3648 DECL_CONTEXT (decl) = DECL_CONTEXT (old);
3649 if (decls_match (decl, old))
3650 return;
3651 }
3652
3653 /* It didn't work, go back to the explicit scope. */
3654 DECL_CONTEXT (decl) = FROB_CONTEXT (scope);
3655 complain:
3656 error ("%qD should have been declared inside %qD", decl, scope);
3657}
3658
3659/* Return the namespace where the current declaration is declared. */
3660
3661tree
3662current_decl_namespace (void)
3663{
3664 tree result;
3665 /* If we have been pushed into a different namespace, use it. */
3666 if (!vec_safe_is_empty (decl_namespace_list))
3667 return decl_namespace_list->last ();
3668
3669 if (current_class_type)
3670 result = decl_namespace_context (current_class_type);
3671 else if (current_function_decl)
3672 result = decl_namespace_context (current_function_decl);
3673 else
3674 result = current_namespace;
3675 return result;
3676}

3678/* Process any ATTRIBUTES on a namespace definition. Returns true if
3679 attribute visibility is seen. */
3680
3681bool
3682handle_namespace_attrs (tree ns, tree attributes)
3683{
3684 tree d;
3685 bool saw_vis = false;
3686
3687 if (attributes == error_mark_node)
3688 return false;
3689
3690 for (d = attributes; d; d = TREE_CHAIN (d))
3691 {
3692 tree name = get_attribute_name (d);
3693 tree args = TREE_VALUE (d);
3694
3695 if (is_attribute_p ("visibility", name))
3696 {
3697 /* attribute visibility is a property of the syntactic block
3698 rather than the namespace as a whole, so we don't touch the
3699 NAMESPACE_DECL at all. */
3700 tree x = args ? TREE_VALUE (args) : NULL_TREE;
3701 if (x == NULL_TREE || TREE_CODE (x) != STRING_CST || TREE_CHAIN (args))
3702 {
3703 warning (OPT_Wattributes,
3704 "%qD attribute requires a single NTBS argument",
3705 name);
3706 continue;
3707 }
3708
3709 if (!TREE_PUBLIC (ns))
3710 warning (OPT_Wattributes,
3711 "%qD attribute is meaningless since members of the "
3712 "anonymous namespace get local symbols", name);
3713
3714 push_visibility (TREE_STRING_POINTER (x), 1);
3715 saw_vis = true;
3716 }
3717 else if (is_attribute_p ("abi_tag", name))
3718 {
3719 if (!DECL_NAMESPACE_ASSOCIATIONS (ns))
3720 {
3721 warning (OPT_Wattributes, "ignoring %qD attribute on non-inline "
3722 "namespace", name);
3723 continue;
3724 }
3725 if (!DECL_NAME (ns))
3726 {
3727 warning (OPT_Wattributes, "ignoring %qD attribute on anonymous "
3728 "namespace", name);
3729 continue;
3730 }
3731 if (!args)
3732 {
3733 tree dn = DECL_NAME (ns);
3734 args = build_string (IDENTIFIER_LENGTH (dn) + 1,
3735 IDENTIFIER_POINTER (dn));
3736 TREE_TYPE (args) = char_array_type_node;
3737 args = fix_string_type (args);
3738 args = build_tree_list (NULL_TREE, args);
3739 }
3740 if (check_abi_tag_args (args, name))
3741 DECL_ATTRIBUTES (ns) = tree_cons (name, args,
3742 DECL_ATTRIBUTES (ns));
3743 }
3744 else
3745 {
3746 warning (OPT_Wattributes, "%qD attribute directive ignored",
3747 name);
3748 continue;
3749 }
3750 }
3751
3752 return saw_vis;
3753}

3755/* Push into the scope of the NAME namespace. If NAME is NULL_TREE, then we
3756 select a name that is unique to this compilation unit. Returns FALSE if
3757 pushdecl fails, TRUE otherwise. */
3758
3759bool
3760push_namespace (tree name)
3761{
3762 tree d = NULL_TREE;
3763 bool need_new = true;
3764 bool implicit_use = false;
3765 bool anon = !name;
3766
3767 bool subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
3768
3769 /* We should not get here if the global_namespace is not yet constructed
3770 nor if NAME designates the global namespace: The global scope is
3771 constructed elsewhere. */
3772 gcc_assert (global_namespace != NULL && name != global_scope_name);
3773
3774 if (anon)
3775 {
3776 name = get_anonymous_namespace_name();
3777 d = IDENTIFIER_NAMESPACE_VALUE (name);
3778 if (d)
3779 /* Reopening anonymous namespace. */
3780 need_new = false;
3781 implicit_use = true;
3782 }
3783 else
3784 {
3785 /* Check whether this is an extended namespace definition. */
3786 d = IDENTIFIER_NAMESPACE_VALUE (name);
3787 if (d != NULL_TREE && TREE_CODE (d) == NAMESPACE_DECL)
3788 {
3789 tree dna = DECL_NAMESPACE_ALIAS (d);
3790 if (dna)
3791 {
3792 /* We do some error recovery for, eg, the redeclaration
3793 of M here:
3794
3795 namespace N {}
3796 namespace M = N;
3797 namespace M {}
3798
3799 However, in nasty cases like:
3800
3801 namespace N
3802 {
3803 namespace M = N;
3804 namespace M {}
3805 }
3806
3807 we just error out below, in duplicate_decls. */
3808 if (NAMESPACE_LEVEL (dna)->level_chain
3809 == current_binding_level)
3810 {
3811 error ("namespace alias %qD not allowed here, "
3812 "assuming %qD", d, dna);
3813 d = dna;
3814 need_new = false;
3815 }
3816 }
3817 else
3818 need_new = false;
3819 }
3820 }
3821
3822 if (need_new)
3823 {
3824 /* Make a new namespace, binding the name to it. */
3825 d = build_lang_decl (NAMESPACE_DECL, name, void_type_node);
3826 DECL_CONTEXT (d) = FROB_CONTEXT (current_namespace);
3827 /* The name of this namespace is not visible to other translation
3828 units if it is an anonymous namespace or member thereof. */
3829 if (anon || decl_anon_ns_mem_p (current_namespace))
3830 TREE_PUBLIC (d) = 0;
3831 else
3832 TREE_PUBLIC (d) = 1;
3833 if (pushdecl (d) == error_mark_node)
3834 {
3835 timevar_cond_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP, subtime);
3836 return false;
3837 }
3838 if (anon)
3839 {
3840 /* Clear DECL_NAME for the benefit of debugging back ends. */
3841 SET_DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (d, name);
3842 DECL_NAME (d) = NULL_TREE;
3843 }
3844 begin_scope (sk_namespace, d);
3845 }
3846 else
3847 resume_scope (NAMESPACE_LEVEL (d));
3848
3849 if (implicit_use)
3850 do_using_directive (d);
3851 /* Enter the name space. */
3852 current_namespace = d;
3853
3854 timevar_cond_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP, subtime);
3855 return true;
3856}
3857
3858/* Pop from the scope of the current namespace. */
3859
3860void
3861pop_namespace (void)
3862{
3863 gcc_assert (current_namespace != global_namespace);
3864 current_namespace = CP_DECL_CONTEXT (current_namespace);
3865 /* The binding level is not popped, as it might be re-opened later. */
3866 leave_scope ();
3867}

3869/* Push into the scope of the namespace NS, even if it is deeply
3870 nested within another namespace. */

3872void
3873push_nested_namespace (tree ns)
3874{
3875 if (ns == global_namespace)
3876 push_to_top_level ();
3877 else
3878 {
3879 push_nested_namespace (CP_DECL_CONTEXT (ns));
3880 push_namespace (DECL_NAME (ns));
3881 }
3882}

3884/* Pop back from the scope of the namespace NS, which was previously
3885 entered with push_nested_namespace. */
3886
3887void
3888pop_nested_namespace (tree ns)
3889{
3890 bool subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
3891 gcc_assert (current_namespace == ns);
3892 while (ns != global_namespace)
3893 {
3894 pop_namespace ();
3895 ns = CP_DECL_CONTEXT (ns);
3896 }
3897
3898 pop_from_top_level ();
3899 timevar_cond_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP, subtime);
3900}

3955

3970/* Like pushdecl, only it places X in the current namespace,
3971 if appropriate. */
3972
3973tree
3974pushdecl_namespace_level (tree x, bool is_friend)
3975{
3976 cp_binding_level *b = current_binding_level;
3977 tree t;
3978
3979 bool subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
3980 t = pushdecl_with_scope (x, NAMESPACE_LEVEL (current_namespace), is_friend);
3981
3982 /* Now, the type_shadowed stack may screw us. Munge it so it does
3983 what we want. */
3984 if (TREE_CODE (t) == TYPE_DECL)
3985 {
3986 tree name = DECL_NAME (t);
3987 tree newval;
3988 tree *ptr = (tree *)0;
3989 for (; !global_scope_p (b); b = b->level_chain)
3990 {
3991 tree shadowed = b->type_shadowed;
3992 for (; shadowed; shadowed = TREE_CHAIN (shadowed))
3993 if (TREE_PURPOSE (shadowed) == name)
3994 {
3995 ptr = &TREE_VALUE (shadowed);
3996 /* Can't break out of the loop here because sometimes
3997 a binding level will have duplicate bindings for
3998 PT names. It's gross, but I haven't time to fix it. */
3999 }
4000 }
4001 newval = TREE_TYPE (t);
4002 if (ptr == (tree *)0)
4003 {
4004 /* @@ This shouldn't be needed. My test case "zstring.cc" trips
4005 up here if this is changed to an assertion. --KR */
4006 SET_IDENTIFIER_TYPE_VALUE (name, t);
4007 }
4008 else
4009 {
4010 *ptr = newval;
4011 }
4012 }
4013 timevar_cond_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP, subtime);
4014 return t;
4015}

4017/* Insert USED into the using list of USER. Set INDIRECT_flag if this
4018 directive is not directly from the source. Also find the common
4019 ancestor and let our users know about the new namespace */
4020
4021static void
4022add_using_namespace_1 (tree user, tree used, bool indirect)
4023{
4024 tree t;
4025 /* Using oneself is a no-op. */
4026 if (user == used)
4027 return;
4028 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (user) == NAMESPACE_DECL);
4029 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (used) == NAMESPACE_DECL);
4030 /* Check if we already have this. */
4031 t = purpose_member (used, DECL_NAMESPACE_USING (user));
4032 if (t != NULL_TREE)
4033 {
4034 if (!indirect)
4035 /* Promote to direct usage. */
4036 TREE_INDIRECT_USING (t) = 0;
4037 return;
4038 }
4039
4040 /* Add used to the user's using list. */
4041 DECL_NAMESPACE_USING (user)
4042 = tree_cons (used, namespace_ancestor (user, used),
4043 DECL_NAMESPACE_USING (user));
4044
4045 TREE_INDIRECT_USING (DECL_NAMESPACE_USING (user)) = indirect;
4046
4047 /* Add user to the used's users list. */
4048 DECL_NAMESPACE_USERS (used)
4049 = tree_cons (user, 0, DECL_NAMESPACE_USERS (used));
4050
4051 /* Recursively add all namespaces used. */
4052 for (t = DECL_NAMESPACE_USING (used); t; t = TREE_CHAIN (t))
4053 /* indirect usage */
4054 add_using_namespace_1 (user, TREE_PURPOSE (t), 1);
4055
4056 /* Tell everyone using us about the new used namespaces. */
4057 for (t = DECL_NAMESPACE_USERS (user); t; t = TREE_CHAIN (t))
4058 add_using_namespace_1 (TREE_PURPOSE (t), used, 1);
4059}
4060
4061/* Wrapper for add_using_namespace_1. */
4062
4063static void
4064add_using_namespace (tree user, tree used, bool indirect)
4065{
4066 bool subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
4067 add_using_namespace_1 (user, used, indirect);
4068 timevar_cond_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP, subtime);
4069}

4071/* Process a using-declaration not appearing in class or local scope. */
4072
4073void
4074do_toplevel_using_decl (tree decl, tree scope, tree name)
4075{
4076 tree oldval, oldtype, newval, newtype;
4077 tree orig_decl = decl;
4078 cxx_binding *binding;
4079
4080 decl = validate_nonmember_using_decl (decl, scope, name);
4081 if (decl == NULL_TREE)
4082 return;
4083
4084 binding = binding_for_name (NAMESPACE_LEVEL (current_namespace), name);
4085
4086 oldval = binding->value;
4087 oldtype = binding->type;
4088
4089 do_nonmember_using_decl (scope, name, oldval, oldtype, &newval, &newtype);
4090
4091 /* Emit debug info. */
4092 if (!processing_template_decl)
4093 cp_emit_debug_info_for_using (orig_decl, current_namespace);

4095 /* Copy declarations found. */
4096 if (newval)
4097 binding->value = newval;
4098 if (newtype)
4099 binding->type = newtype;

4102/* Process a using-directive. */
4103
4104void
4105do_using_directive (tree name_space)
4106{
4107 tree context = NULL_TREE;
4108
4109 if (name_space == error_mark_node)
4110 return;
4111
4112 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (name_space) == NAMESPACE_DECL);
4113
4114 if (building_stmt_list_p ())
4115 add_stmt (build_stmt (input_location, USING_STMT, name_space));
4116 name_space = ORIGINAL_NAMESPACE (name_space);
4117
4118 if (!toplevel_bindings_p ())
4119 {
4120 push_using_directive (name_space);
4121 }
4122 else
4123 {
4124 /* direct usage */
4125 add_using_namespace (current_namespace, name_space, 0);
4126 if (current_namespace != global_namespace)
4127 context = current_namespace;
4128
4129 /* Emit debugging info. */
4130 if (!processing_template_decl)
4131 (*debug_hooks->imported_module_or_decl) (name_space, NULL_TREE,
4132 context, false);
4133 }
4134}

4136/* Deal with a using-directive seen by the parser. Currently we only
4137 handle attributes here, since they cannot appear inside a template. */
4138
4139void
4140parse_using_directive (tree name_space, tree attribs)
4141{
4142 do_using_directive (name_space);
4143
4144 if (attribs == error_mark_node)
4145 return;
4146
4147 for (tree a = attribs; a; a = TREE_CHAIN (a))
4148 {
4149 tree name = get_attribute_name (a);
4150 if (is_attribute_p ("strong", name))
4151 {
4152 warning (OPT_Wdeprecated, "strong using is deprecated; use inline "
4153 "namespaces instead");
4154 if (!toplevel_bindings_p ())
4155 error ("strong using only meaningful at namespace scope");
4156 else if (name_space != error_mark_node)
4157 {
4158 if (!is_ancestor (current_namespace, name_space))
4159 error ("current namespace %qD does not enclose strongly used namespace %qD",
4160 current_namespace, name_space);
4161 DECL_NAMESPACE_ASSOCIATIONS (name_space)
4162 = tree_cons (current_namespace, 0,
4163 DECL_NAMESPACE_ASSOCIATIONS (name_space));
4164 }
4165 }
4166 else
4167 warning (OPT_Wattributes, "%qD attribute directive ignored", name);
4168 }
4169}

4213
4214/* Combines two sets of overloaded functions into an OVERLOAD chain, removing
4215 duplicates. The first list becomes the tail of the result.
4216
4217 The algorithm is O(n^2). We could get this down to O(n log n) by
4218 doing a sort on the addresses of the functions, if that becomes
4219 necessary. */
4220
4221static tree
4222merge_functions (tree s1, tree s2)
4223{
4224 for (; s2; s2 = OVL_NEXT (s2))
4225 {
4226 tree fn2 = OVL_CURRENT (s2);
4227 tree fns1;
4228
4229 for (fns1 = s1; fns1; fns1 = OVL_NEXT (fns1))
4230 {
4231 tree fn1 = OVL_CURRENT (fns1);
4232
4233 /* If the function from S2 is already in S1, there is no
4234 need to add it again. For `extern "C"' functions, we
4235 might have two FUNCTION_DECLs for the same function, in
4236 different namespaces, but let's leave them in case
4237 they have different default arguments. */
4238 if (fn1 == fn2)
4239 break;
4240 }
4241
4242 /* If we exhausted all of the functions in S1, FN2 is new. */
4243 if (!fns1)
4244 s1 = build_overload (fn2, s1);
4245 }
4246 return s1;
4247}
4248
4249/* Returns TRUE iff OLD and NEW are the same entity.
4250
4251 3 [basic]/3: An entity is a value, object, reference, function,
4252 enumerator, type, class member, template, template specialization,
4253 namespace, parameter pack, or this.
4254
4255 7.3.4 [namespace.udir]/4: If name lookup finds a declaration for a name
4256 in two different namespaces, and the declarations do not declare the
4257 same entity and do not declare functions, the use of the name is
4258 ill-formed. */
4259
4260static bool
4261same_entity_p (tree one, tree two)
4262{
4263 if (one == two)
4264 return true;
4265 if (!one || !two)
4266 return false;
4267 if (TREE_CODE (one) == TYPE_DECL
4268 && TREE_CODE (two) == TYPE_DECL
4269 && same_type_p (TREE_TYPE (one), TREE_TYPE (two)))
4270 return true;
4271 return false;
4272}
4273
4274/* This should return an error not all definitions define functions.
4275 It is not an error if we find two functions with exactly the
4276 same signature, only if these are selected in overload resolution.
4277 old is the current set of bindings, new_binding the freshly-found binding.
4278 XXX Do we want to give *all* candidates in case of ambiguity?
4279 XXX In what way should I treat extern declarations?
4280 XXX I don't want to repeat the entire duplicate_decls here */
4281
4282static void
4283ambiguous_decl (struct scope_binding *old, cxx_binding *new_binding, int flags)
4284{
4285 tree val, type;
4286 gcc_assert (old != NULL);
4287
4288 /* Copy the type. */
4289 type = new_binding->type;
4290 if (LOOKUP_NAMESPACES_ONLY (flags)
4291 || (type && hidden_name_p (type) && !(flags & LOOKUP_HIDDEN)))
4292 type = NULL_TREE;
4293
4294 /* Copy the value. */
4295 val = new_binding->value;
4296 if (val)
4297 {
4298 if (!(flags & LOOKUP_HIDDEN))
4299 val = remove_hidden_names (val);
4300 if (val)
4301 switch (TREE_CODE (val))
4302 {
4303 case TEMPLATE_DECL:
4304 /* If we expect types or namespaces, and not templates,
4305 or this is not a template class. */
4306 if ((LOOKUP_QUALIFIERS_ONLY (flags)
4307 && !DECL_TYPE_TEMPLATE_P (val)))
4308 val = NULL_TREE;
4309 break;
4310 case TYPE_DECL:
4311 if (LOOKUP_NAMESPACES_ONLY (flags)
4312 || (type && (flags & LOOKUP_PREFER_TYPES)))
4313 val = NULL_TREE;
4314 break;
4315 case NAMESPACE_DECL:
4316 if (LOOKUP_TYPES_ONLY (flags))
4317 val = NULL_TREE;
4318 break;
4319 case FUNCTION_DECL:
4320 /* Ignore built-in functions that are still anticipated. */
4321 if (LOOKUP_QUALIFIERS_ONLY (flags))
4322 val = NULL_TREE;
4323 break;
4324 default:
4325 if (LOOKUP_QUALIFIERS_ONLY (flags))
4326 val = NULL_TREE;
4327 }
4328 }
4329
4330 /* If val is hidden, shift down any class or enumeration name. */
4331 if (!val)
4332 {
4333 val = type;
4334 type = NULL_TREE;
4335 }
4336
4337 if (!old->value)
4338 old->value = val;
4339 else if (val && !same_entity_p (val, old->value))
4340 {
4341 if (is_overloaded_fn (old->value) && is_overloaded_fn (val))
4342 old->value = merge_functions (old->value, val);
4343 else
4344 {
4345 old->value = tree_cons (NULL_TREE, old->value,
4346 build_tree_list (NULL_TREE, val));
4347 TREE_TYPE (old->value) = error_mark_node;
4348 }
4349 }
4350
4351 if (!old->type)
4352 old->type = type;
4353 else if (type && old->type != type)
4354 {
4355 old->type = tree_cons (NULL_TREE, old->type,
4356 build_tree_list (NULL_TREE, type));
4357 TREE_TYPE (old->type) = error_mark_node;
4358 }
4359}

4362
4363tree
4364cp_namespace_decls (tree ns)
4365{
4366 return NAMESPACE_LEVEL (ns)->names;

4369/* Combine prefer_type and namespaces_only into flags. */
4370
4371static int
4372lookup_flags (int prefer_type, int namespaces_only)
4373{
4374 if (namespaces_only)
4375 return LOOKUP_PREFER_NAMESPACES;
4376 if (prefer_type > 1)
4377 return LOOKUP_PREFER_TYPES;
4378 if (prefer_type > 0)
4379 return LOOKUP_PREFER_BOTH;
4380 return 0;
4381}
4382
4383/* Given a lookup that returned VAL, use FLAGS to decide if we want to
4384 ignore it or not. Subroutine of lookup_name_real and
4385 lookup_type_scope. */
4386
4387static bool
4388qualify_lookup (tree val, int flags)
4389{
4390 if (val == NULL_TREE)
4391 return false;
4392 if ((flags & LOOKUP_PREFER_NAMESPACES) && TREE_CODE (val) == NAMESPACE_DECL)
4393 return true;
4394 if (flags & LOOKUP_PREFER_TYPES)
4395 {
4396 tree target_val = strip_using_decl (val);
4397 if (TREE_CODE (target_val) == TYPE_DECL
4398 || TREE_CODE (target_val) == TEMPLATE_DECL)
4399 return true;
4400 }
4401 if (flags & (LOOKUP_PREFER_NAMESPACES | LOOKUP_PREFER_TYPES))
4402 return false;
4403 /* Look through lambda things that we shouldn't be able to see. */
4404 if (is_lambda_ignored_entity (val))
4405 return false;
4406 return true;
4407}
4408
4409/* Given a lookup that returned VAL, decide if we want to ignore it or
4410 not based on DECL_ANTICIPATED. */
4411
4412bool
4413hidden_name_p (tree val)
4414{
4415 if (DECL_P (val)
4416 && DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (val)
4417 && TYPE_FUNCTION_OR_TEMPLATE_DECL_P (val)
4418 && DECL_ANTICIPATED (val))
4419 return true;
4420 if (TREE_CODE (val) == OVERLOAD)
4421 {
4422 for (tree o = val; o; o = OVL_CHAIN (o))
4423 if (!hidden_name_p (OVL_FUNCTION (o)))
4424 return false;
4425 return true;
4426 }
4427 return false;
4428}
4429
4430/* Remove any hidden declarations from a possibly overloaded set
4431 of functions. */
4432
4433tree
4434remove_hidden_names (tree fns)
4435{
4436 if (!fns)
4437 return fns;
4438
4439 if (DECL_P (fns) && hidden_name_p (fns))
4440 fns = NULL_TREE;
4441 else if (TREE_CODE (fns) == OVERLOAD)
4442 {
4443 tree o;
4444
4445 for (o = fns; o; o = OVL_NEXT (o))
4446 if (hidden_name_p (OVL_CURRENT (o)))
4447 break;
4448 if (o)
4449 {
4450 tree n = NULL_TREE;
4451
4452 for (o = fns; o; o = OVL_NEXT (o))
4453 if (!hidden_name_p (OVL_CURRENT (o)))
4454 n = build_overload (OVL_CURRENT (o), n);
4455 fns = n;
4456 }
4457 }
4458
4459 return fns;
4460}
4461
4462/* Suggest alternatives for NAME, an IDENTIFIER_NODE for which name
4463 lookup failed. Search through all available namespaces and print out
4464 possible candidates. If no exact matches are found, and
4465 SUGGEST_MISSPELLINGS is true, then also look for near-matches and
4466 suggest the best near-match, if there is one. */
4467
4468void
4469suggest_alternatives_for (location_t location, tree name,
4470 bool suggest_misspellings)
4471{
4472 vec<tree> candidates = vNULL;
4473 vec<tree> namespaces_to_search = vNULL;
4474 int max_to_search = PARAM_VALUE (CXX_MAX_NAMESPACES_FOR_DIAGNOSTIC_HELP);
4475 int n_searched = 0;
4476 tree t;
4477 unsigned ix;
4478
4479 namespaces_to_search.safe_push (global_namespace);
4480
4481 while (!namespaces_to_search.is_empty ()
4482 && n_searched < max_to_search)
4483 {
4484 tree scope = namespaces_to_search.pop ();
4485 struct scope_binding binding = EMPTY_SCOPE_BINDING;
4486 cp_binding_level *level = NAMESPACE_LEVEL (scope);
4487
4488 /* Look in this namespace. */
4489 qualified_lookup_using_namespace (name, scope, &binding, 0);
4490
4491 n_searched++;
4492
4493 if (binding.value)
4494 candidates.safe_push (binding.value);
4495
4496 /* Add child namespaces. */
4497 for (t = level->namespaces; t; t = DECL_CHAIN (t))
4498 namespaces_to_search.safe_push (t);
4499 }
4500
4501 /* If we stopped before we could examine all namespaces, inform the
4502 user. Do this even if we don't have any candidates, since there
4503 might be more candidates further down that we weren't able to
4504 find. */
4505 if (n_searched >= max_to_search
4506 && !namespaces_to_search.is_empty ())
4507 inform (location,
4508 "maximum limit of %d namespaces searched for %qE",
4509 max_to_search, name);
4510
4511 namespaces_to_search.release ();
4512
4513 /* Nothing useful to report for NAME. Report on likely misspellings,
4514 or do nothing. */
4515 if (candidates.is_empty ())
4516 {
4517 if (suggest_misspellings)
4518 {
4519 const char *fuzzy_name = lookup_name_fuzzy (name, FUZZY_LOOKUP_NAME);
4520 if (fuzzy_name)
4521 {
4522 gcc_rich_location richloc (location);
4523 richloc.add_fixit_replace (fuzzy_name);
4524 inform_at_rich_loc (&richloc, "suggested alternative: %qs",
4525 fuzzy_name);
4526 }
4527 }
4528 return;
4529 }
4530
4531 inform_n (location, candidates.length (),
4532 "suggested alternative:",
4533 "suggested alternatives:");
4534
4535 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (candidates, ix, t)
4536 inform (location_of (t), " %qE", t);
4537
4538 candidates.release ();
4539}
4540
4541/* Look for alternatives for NAME, an IDENTIFIER_NODE for which name
4542 lookup failed within the explicitly provided SCOPE. Suggest the
4543 the best meaningful candidates (if any) as a fix-it hint.
4544 Return true iff a suggestion was provided. */
4545
4546bool
4547suggest_alternative_in_explicit_scope (location_t location, tree name,
4548 tree scope)
4549{
4550 /* Resolve any namespace aliases. */
4551 scope = ORIGINAL_NAMESPACE (scope);
4552
4553 cp_binding_level *level = NAMESPACE_LEVEL (scope);
4554
4555 best_match <tree, tree> bm (name);
4556 consider_binding_level (name, bm, level, false, FUZZY_LOOKUP_NAME);
4557
4558 /* See if we have a good suggesion for the user. */
4559 tree best_id = bm.get_best_meaningful_candidate ();
4560 if (best_id)
4561 {
4562 const char *fuzzy_name = IDENTIFIER_POINTER (best_id);
4563 gcc_rich_location richloc (location);
4564 richloc.add_fixit_replace (fuzzy_name);
4565 inform_at_rich_loc (&richloc, "suggested alternative: %qs",
4566 fuzzy_name);
4567 return true;
4568 }
4569
4570 return false;
4571}
4572
4573/* Unscoped lookup of a global: iterate over current namespaces,
4574 considering using-directives. */
4575
4576static tree
4577unqualified_namespace_lookup_1 (tree name, int flags)
4578{
4579 tree initial = current_decl_namespace ();
4580 tree scope = initial;
4581 tree siter;
4582 cp_binding_level *level;
4583 tree val = NULL_TREE;
4584
4585 for (; !val; scope = CP_DECL_CONTEXT (scope))
4586 {
4587 struct scope_binding binding = EMPTY_SCOPE_BINDING;
4588 cxx_binding *b =
4589 cp_binding_level_find_binding_for_name (NAMESPACE_LEVEL (scope), name);
4590
4591 if (b)
4592 ambiguous_decl (&binding, b, flags);
4593
4594 /* Add all _DECLs seen through local using-directives. */
4595 for (level = current_binding_level;
4596 level->kind != sk_namespace;
4597 level = level->level_chain)
4598 if (!lookup_using_namespace (name, &binding, level->using_directives,
4599 scope, flags))
4600 /* Give up because of error. */
4601 return error_mark_node;
4602
4603 /* Add all _DECLs seen through global using-directives. */
4604 /* XXX local and global using lists should work equally. */
4605 siter = initial;
4606 while (1)
4607 {
4608 if (!lookup_using_namespace (name, &binding,
4609 DECL_NAMESPACE_USING (siter),
4610 scope, flags))
4611 /* Give up because of error. */
4612 return error_mark_node;
4613 if (siter == scope) break;
4614 siter = CP_DECL_CONTEXT (siter);
4615 }
4616
4617 val = binding.value;
4618 if (scope == global_namespace)
4619 break;
4620 }
4621 return val;
4622}
4623
4624/* Wrapper for unqualified_namespace_lookup_1. */
4625
4626static tree
4627unqualified_namespace_lookup (tree name, int flags)
4628{
4629 tree ret;
4630 bool subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
4631 ret = unqualified_namespace_lookup_1 (name, flags);
4632 timevar_cond_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP, subtime);
4633 return ret;
4634}

4636/* Look up NAME (an IDENTIFIER_NODE) in SCOPE (either a NAMESPACE_DECL
4637 or a class TYPE).
4638
4639 If PREFER_TYPE is > 0, we only return TYPE_DECLs or namespaces.
4640 If PREFER_TYPE is > 1, we only return TYPE_DECLs.
4641
4642 Returns a DECL (or OVERLOAD, or BASELINK) representing the
4643 declaration found. If no suitable declaration can be found,
4644 ERROR_MARK_NODE is returned. If COMPLAIN is true and SCOPE is
4645 neither a class-type nor a namespace a diagnostic is issued. */
4646
4647tree
4648lookup_qualified_name (tree scope, tree name, int prefer_type, bool complain,
4649 bool find_hidden)
4650{
4651 tree t = NULL_TREE;
4652
4653 if (TREE_CODE (scope) == NAMESPACE_DECL)
4654 {
4655 struct scope_binding binding = EMPTY_SCOPE_BINDING;
4656
4657 int flags = lookup_flags (prefer_type, /*namespaces_only*/false);
4658 if (find_hidden)
4659 flags |= LOOKUP_HIDDEN;
4660 if (qualified_lookup_using_namespace (name, scope, &binding, flags))
4661 t = binding.value;
4662 }
4663 else if (cxx_dialect != cxx98 && TREE_CODE (scope) == ENUMERAL_TYPE)
4664 t = lookup_enumerator (scope, name);
4665 else if (is_class_type (scope, complain))
4666 t = lookup_member (scope, name, 2, prefer_type, tf_warning_or_error);
4667
4668 if (!t)
4669 return error_mark_node;
4670 return t;
4671}
4672
4673/* Subroutine of unqualified_namespace_lookup:
4674 Add the bindings of NAME in used namespaces to VAL.
4675 We are currently looking for names in namespace SCOPE, so we
4676 look through USINGS for using-directives of namespaces
4677 which have SCOPE as a common ancestor with the current scope.
4678 Returns false on errors. */
4679
4680static bool
4681lookup_using_namespace (tree name, struct scope_binding *val,
4682 tree usings, tree scope, int flags)
4683{
4684 tree iter;
4685 bool subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
4686 /* Iterate over all used namespaces in current, searching for using
4687 directives of scope. */
4688 for (iter = usings; iter; iter = TREE_CHAIN (iter))
4689 if (TREE_VALUE (iter) == scope)
4690 {
4691 tree used = ORIGINAL_NAMESPACE (TREE_PURPOSE (iter));
4692 cxx_binding *val1 =
4693 cp_binding_level_find_binding_for_name (NAMESPACE_LEVEL (used), name);
4694 /* Resolve ambiguities. */
4695 if (val1)
4696 ambiguous_decl (val, val1, flags);
4697 }
4698 timevar_cond_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP, subtime);
4699 return val->value != error_mark_node;
4700}

4702/* Returns true iff VEC contains TARGET. */
4703
4704static bool
4705tree_vec_contains (vec<tree, va_gc> *vec, tree target)
4706{
4707 unsigned int i;
4708 tree elt;
4709 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (vec,i,elt)
4710 if (elt == target)
4711 return true;
4712 return false;
4713}
4714
4715/* [namespace.qual]
4716 Accepts the NAME to lookup and its qualifying SCOPE.
4717 Returns the name/type pair found into the cxx_binding *RESULT,
4718 or false on error. */
4719
4720static bool
4721qualified_lookup_using_namespace (tree name, tree scope,
4722 struct scope_binding *result, int flags)
4723{
4724 /* Maintain a list of namespaces visited... */
4725 vec<tree, va_gc> *seen = NULL;
4726 vec<tree, va_gc> *seen_inline = NULL;
4727 /* ... and a list of namespace yet to see. */
4728 vec<tree, va_gc> *todo = NULL;
4729 vec<tree, va_gc> *todo_maybe = NULL;
4730 vec<tree, va_gc> *todo_inline = NULL;
4731 tree usings;
4732 timevar_start (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
4733 /* Look through namespace aliases. */
4734 scope = ORIGINAL_NAMESPACE (scope);
4735
4736 query_oracle (name);
4737
4738 /* Algorithm: Starting with SCOPE, walk through the set of used
4739 namespaces. For each used namespace, look through its inline
4740 namespace set for any bindings and usings. If no bindings are
4741 found, add any usings seen to the set of used namespaces. */
4742 vec_safe_push (todo, scope);
4743
4744 while (todo->length ())
4745 {
4746 bool found_here;
4747 scope = todo->pop ();
4748 if (tree_vec_contains (seen, scope))
4749 continue;
4750 vec_safe_push (seen, scope);
4751 vec_safe_push (todo_inline, scope);
4752
4753 found_here = false;
4754 while (todo_inline->length ())
4755 {
4756 cxx_binding *binding;
4757
4758 scope = todo_inline->pop ();
4759 if (tree_vec_contains (seen_inline, scope))
4760 continue;
4761 vec_safe_push (seen_inline, scope);
4762
4763 binding =
4764 cp_binding_level_find_binding_for_name (NAMESPACE_LEVEL (scope), name);
4765 if (binding)
4766 {
4767 ambiguous_decl (result, binding, flags);
4768 if (result->type || result->value)
4769 found_here = true;
4770 }
4771
4772 for (usings = DECL_NAMESPACE_USING (scope); usings;
4773 usings = TREE_CHAIN (usings))
4774 if (!TREE_INDIRECT_USING (usings))
4775 {
4776 if (is_associated_namespace (scope, TREE_PURPOSE (usings)))
4777 vec_safe_push (todo_inline, TREE_PURPOSE (usings));
4778 else
4779 vec_safe_push (todo_maybe, TREE_PURPOSE (usings));
4780 }
4781 }
4782
4783 if (found_here)
4784 vec_safe_truncate (todo_maybe, 0);
4785 else
4786 while (vec_safe_length (todo_maybe))
4787 vec_safe_push (todo, todo_maybe->pop ());
4788 }
4789 vec_free (todo);
4790 vec_free (todo_maybe);
4791 vec_free (todo_inline);
4792 vec_free (seen);
4793 vec_free (seen_inline);
4794 timevar_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
4795 return result->value != error_mark_node;
4796}
4797
4798/* Helper function for lookup_name_fuzzy.
4799 Traverse binding level LVL, looking for good name matches for NAME
4800 (and BM). */
4801static void
4802consider_binding_level (tree name, best_match <tree, tree> &bm,
4803 cp_binding_level *lvl, bool look_within_fields,
4804 enum lookup_name_fuzzy_kind kind)
4805{
4806 if (look_within_fields)
4807 if (lvl->this_entity && TREE_CODE (lvl->this_entity) == RECORD_TYPE)
4808 {
4809 tree type = lvl->this_entity;
4810 bool want_type_p = (kind == FUZZY_LOOKUP_TYPENAME);
4811 tree best_matching_field
4812 = lookup_member_fuzzy (type, name, want_type_p);
4813 if (best_matching_field)
4814 bm.consider (best_matching_field);
4815 }
4816
4817 for (tree t = lvl->names; t; t = TREE_CHAIN (t))
4818 {
4819 tree d = t;
4820
4821 /* OVERLOADs or decls from using declaration are wrapped into
4822 TREE_LIST. */
4823 if (TREE_CODE (d) == TREE_LIST)
4824 {
4825 d = TREE_VALUE (d);
4826 d = OVL_CURRENT (d);
4827 }
4828
4829 /* Don't use bindings from implicitly declared functions,
4830 as they were likely misspellings themselves. */
4831 if (TREE_TYPE (d) == error_mark_node)
4832 continue;
4833
4834 /* Skip anticipated decls of builtin functions. */
4835 if (TREE_CODE (d) == FUNCTION_DECL
4836 && DECL_BUILT_IN (d)
4837 && DECL_ANTICIPATED (d))
4838 continue;
4839
4840 if (tree name = DECL_NAME (d))
4841 /* Ignore internal names with spaces in them. */
4842 if (!strchr (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (name), ' '))
4843 bm.consider (DECL_NAME (d));
4844 }
4845}
4846
4847/* Search for near-matches for NAME within the current bindings, and within
4848 macro names, returning the best match as a const char *, or NULL if
4849 no reasonable match is found. */
4850
4851const char *
4852lookup_name_fuzzy (tree name, enum lookup_name_fuzzy_kind kind)
4853{
4854 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (name) == IDENTIFIER_NODE);
4855
4856 best_match <tree, tree> bm (name);
4857
4858 cp_binding_level *lvl;
4859 for (lvl = scope_chain->class_bindings; lvl; lvl = lvl->level_chain)
4860 consider_binding_level (name, bm, lvl, true, kind);
4861
4862 for (lvl = current_binding_level; lvl; lvl = lvl->level_chain)
4863 consider_binding_level (name, bm, lvl, false, kind);
4864
4865 /* Consider macros: if the user misspelled a macro name e.g. "SOME_MACRO"
4866 as:
4867 x = SOME_OTHER_MACRO (y);
4868 then "SOME_OTHER_MACRO" will survive to the frontend and show up
4869 as a misspelled identifier.
4870
4871 Use the best distance so far so that a candidate is only set if
4872 a macro is better than anything so far. This allows early rejection
4873 (without calculating the edit distance) of macro names that must have
4874 distance >= bm.get_best_distance (), and means that we only get a
4875 non-NULL result for best_macro_match if it's better than any of
4876 the identifiers already checked. */
4877 best_macro_match bmm (name, bm.get_best_distance (), parse_in);
4878 cpp_hashnode *best_macro = bmm.get_best_meaningful_candidate ();
4879 /* If a macro is the closest so far to NAME, suggest it. */
4880 if (best_macro)
4881 return (const char *)best_macro->ident.str;
4882
4883 /* Try the "starts_decl_specifier_p" keywords to detect
4884 "singed" vs "signed" typos. */
4885 for (unsigned i = 0; i < num_c_common_reswords; i++)
4886 {
4887 const c_common_resword *resword = &c_common_reswords[i];
4888
4889 if (!cp_keyword_starts_decl_specifier_p (resword->rid))
4890 continue;
4891
4892 tree resword_identifier = ridpointers [resword->rid];
4893 if (!resword_identifier)
4894 continue;
4895 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (resword_identifier) == IDENTIFIER_NODE);
4896
4897 /* Only consider reserved words that survived the
4898 filtering in init_reswords (e.g. for -std). */
4899 if (!C_IS_RESERVED_WORD (resword_identifier))
4900 continue;
4901
4902 bm.consider (resword_identifier);
4903 }
4904
4905 /* See if we have a good suggesion for the user. */
4906 tree best_id = bm.get_best_meaningful_candidate ();
4907 if (best_id)
4908 return IDENTIFIER_POINTER (best_id);
4909
4910 /* No meaningful suggestion available. */
4911 return NULL;
4912}
4913
4914/* Subroutine of outer_binding.
4915
4916 Returns TRUE if BINDING is a binding to a template parameter of
4917 SCOPE. In that case SCOPE is the scope of a primary template
4918 parameter -- in the sense of G++, i.e, a template that has its own
4919 template header.
4920
4921 Returns FALSE otherwise. */
4922
4923static bool
4924binding_to_template_parms_of_scope_p (cxx_binding *binding,
4925 cp_binding_level *scope)
4926{
4927 tree binding_value, tmpl, tinfo;
4928 int level;
4929
4930 if (!binding || !scope || !scope->this_entity)
4931 return false;
4932
4933 binding_value = binding->value ? binding->value : binding->type;
4934 tinfo = get_template_info (scope->this_entity);
4935
4936 /* BINDING_VALUE must be a template parm. */
4937 if (binding_value == NULL_TREE
4938 || (!DECL_P (binding_value)
4939 || !DECL_TEMPLATE_PARM_P (binding_value)))
4940 return false;
4941
4942 /* The level of BINDING_VALUE. */
4943 level =
4944 template_type_parameter_p (binding_value)
4945 ? TEMPLATE_PARM_LEVEL (TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM_INDEX
4946 (TREE_TYPE (binding_value)))
4947 : TEMPLATE_PARM_LEVEL (DECL_INITIAL (binding_value));
4948
4949 /* The template of the current scope, iff said scope is a primary
4950 template. */
4951 tmpl = (tinfo
4952 && PRIMARY_TEMPLATE_P (TI_TEMPLATE (tinfo))
4953 ? TI_TEMPLATE (tinfo)
4954 : NULL_TREE);
4955
4956 /* If the level of the parm BINDING_VALUE equals the depth of TMPL,
4957 then BINDING_VALUE is a parameter of TMPL. */
4958 return (tmpl && level == TMPL_PARMS_DEPTH (DECL_TEMPLATE_PARMS (tmpl)));
4959}
4960
4961/* Return the innermost non-namespace binding for NAME from a scope
4962 containing BINDING, or, if BINDING is NULL, the current scope.
4963 Please note that for a given template, the template parameters are
4964 considered to be in the scope containing the current scope.
4965 If CLASS_P is false, then class bindings are ignored. */
4966
4967cxx_binding *
4968outer_binding (tree name,
4969 cxx_binding *binding,
4970 bool class_p)
4971{
4972 cxx_binding *outer;
4973 cp_binding_level *scope;
4974 cp_binding_level *outer_scope;
4975
4976 if (binding)
4977 {
4978 scope = binding->scope->level_chain;
4979 outer = binding->previous;
4980 }
4981 else
4982 {
4983 scope = current_binding_level;
4984 outer = IDENTIFIER_BINDING (name);
4985 }
4986 outer_scope = outer ? outer->scope : NULL;
4987
4988 /* Because we create class bindings lazily, we might be missing a
4989 class binding for NAME. If there are any class binding levels
4990 between the LAST_BINDING_LEVEL and the scope in which OUTER was
4991 declared, we must lookup NAME in those class scopes. */
4992 if (class_p)
4993 while (scope && scope != outer_scope && scope->kind != sk_namespace)
4994 {
4995 if (scope->kind == sk_class)
4996 {
4997 cxx_binding *class_binding;
4998
4999 class_binding = get_class_binding (name, scope);
5000 if (class_binding)
5001 {
5002 /* Thread this new class-scope binding onto the
5003 IDENTIFIER_BINDING list so that future lookups
5004 find it quickly. */
5005 class_binding->previous = outer;
5006 if (binding)
5007 binding->previous = class_binding;
5008 else
5009 IDENTIFIER_BINDING (name) = class_binding;
5010 return class_binding;
5011 }
5012 }
5013 /* If we are in a member template, the template parms of the member
5014 template are considered to be inside the scope of the containing
5015 class, but within G++ the class bindings are all pushed between the
5016 template parms and the function body. So if the outer binding is
5017 a template parm for the current scope, return it now rather than
5018 look for a class binding. */
5019 if (outer_scope && outer_scope->kind == sk_template_parms
5020 && binding_to_template_parms_of_scope_p (outer, scope))
5021 return outer;
5022
5023 scope = scope->level_chain;
5024 }
5025
5026 return outer;
5027}

5029/* Return the innermost block-scope or class-scope value binding for
5030 NAME, or NULL_TREE if there is no such binding. */
5031
5032tree
5033innermost_non_namespace_value (tree name)
5034{
5035 cxx_binding *binding;
5036 binding = outer_binding (name, /*binding=*/NULL, /*class_p=*/true);
5037 return binding ? binding->value : NULL_TREE;
5038}
5039
5040/* Look up NAME in the current binding level and its superiors in the
5041 namespace of variables, functions and typedefs. Return a ..._DECL
5042 node of some kind representing its definition if there is only one
5043 such declaration, or return a TREE_LIST with all the overloaded
5044 definitions if there are many, or return 0 if it is undefined.
5045 Hidden name, either friend declaration or built-in function, are
5046 not ignored.
5047
5048 If PREFER_TYPE is > 0, we prefer TYPE_DECLs or namespaces.
5049 If PREFER_TYPE is > 1, we reject non-type decls (e.g. namespaces).
5050 Otherwise we prefer non-TYPE_DECLs.
5051
5052 If NONCLASS is nonzero, bindings in class scopes are ignored. If
5053 BLOCK_P is false, bindings in block scopes are ignored. */
5054
5055static tree
5056lookup_name_real_1 (tree name, int prefer_type, int nonclass, bool block_p,
5057 int namespaces_only, int flags)
5058{
5059 cxx_binding *iter;
5060 tree val = NULL_TREE;
5061
5062 query_oracle (name);
5063
5064 /* Conversion operators are handled specially because ordinary
5065 unqualified name lookup will not find template conversion
5066 operators. */
5067 if (IDENTIFIER_TYPENAME_P (name))
5068 {
5069 cp_binding_level *level;
5070
5071 for (level = current_binding_level;
5072 level && level->kind != sk_namespace;
5073 level = level->level_chain)
5074 {
5075 tree class_type;
5076 tree operators;
5077
5078 /* A conversion operator can only be declared in a class
5079 scope. */
5080 if (level->kind != sk_class)
5081 continue;
5082
5083 /* Lookup the conversion operator in the class. */
5084 class_type = level->this_entity;
5085 operators = lookup_fnfields (class_type, name, /*protect=*/0);
5086 if (operators)
5087 return operators;
5088 }
5089
5090 return NULL_TREE;
5091 }
5092
5093 flags |= lookup_flags (prefer_type, namespaces_only);
5094
5095 /* First, look in non-namespace scopes. */
5096
5097 if (current_class_type == NULL_TREE)
5098 nonclass = 1;
5099
5100 if (block_p || !nonclass)
5101 for (iter = outer_binding (name, NULL, !nonclass);
5102 iter;
5103 iter = outer_binding (name, iter, !nonclass))
5104 {
5105 tree binding;
5106
5107 /* Skip entities we don't want. */
5108 if (LOCAL_BINDING_P (iter) ? !block_p : nonclass)
5109 continue;
5110
5111 /* If this is the kind of thing we're looking for, we're done. */
5112 if (qualify_lookup (iter->value, flags))
5113 binding = iter->value;
5114 else if ((flags & LOOKUP_PREFER_TYPES)
5115 && qualify_lookup (iter->type, flags))
5116 binding = iter->type;
5117 else
5118 binding = NULL_TREE;
5119
5120 if (binding)
5121 {
5122 if (hidden_name_p (binding))
5123 {
5124 /* A non namespace-scope binding can only be hidden in the
5125 presence of a local class, due to friend declarations.
5126
5127 In particular, consider:
5128
5129 struct C;
5130 void f() {
5131 struct A {
5132 friend struct B;
5133 friend struct C;
5134 void g() {
5135 B* b; // error: B is hidden
5136 C* c; // OK, finds ::C
5137 }
5138 };
5139 B *b; // error: B is hidden
5140 C *c; // OK, finds ::C
5141 struct B {};
5142 B *bb; // OK
5143 }
5144
5145 The standard says that "B" is a local class in "f"
5146 (but not nested within "A") -- but that name lookup
5147 for "B" does not find this declaration until it is
5148 declared directly with "f".
5149
5150 In particular:
5151
5152 [class.friend]
5153
5154 If a friend declaration appears in a local class and
5155 the name specified is an unqualified name, a prior
5156 declaration is looked up without considering scopes
5157 that are outside the innermost enclosing non-class
5158 scope. For a friend function declaration, if there is
5159 no prior declaration, the program is ill-formed. For a
5160 friend class declaration, if there is no prior
5161 declaration, the class that is specified belongs to the
5162 innermost enclosing non-class scope, but if it is
5163 subsequently referenced, its name is not found by name
5164 lookup until a matching declaration is provided in the
5165 innermost enclosing nonclass scope.
5166
5167 So just keep looking for a non-hidden binding.
5168 */
5169 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (binding) == TYPE_DECL);
5170 continue;
5171 }
5172 val = binding;
5173 break;
5174 }
5175 }
5176
5177 /* Now lookup in namespace scopes. */
5178 if (!val)
5179 val = unqualified_namespace_lookup (name, flags);
5180
5181 /* Anticipated built-ins and friends aren't found by normal lookup. */
5182 if (val && !(flags & LOOKUP_HIDDEN))
5183 val = remove_hidden_names (val);
5184
5185 /* If we have a single function from a using decl, pull it out. */
5186 if (val && TREE_CODE (val) == OVERLOAD && !really_overloaded_fn (val))
5187 val = OVL_FUNCTION (val);
5188
5189 return val;
5190}

5233/* Look up NAME for type used in elaborated name specifier in
5234 the scopes given by SCOPE. SCOPE can be either TS_CURRENT or
5235 TS_WITHIN_ENCLOSING_NON_CLASS. Although not implied by the
5236 name, more scopes are checked if cleanup or template parameter
5237 scope is encountered.
5238
5239 Unlike lookup_name_real, we make sure that NAME is actually
5240 declared in the desired scope, not from inheritance, nor using
5241 directive. For using declaration, there is DR138 still waiting
5242 to be resolved. Hidden name coming from an earlier friend
5243 declaration is also returned.
5244
5245 A TYPE_DECL best matching the NAME is returned. Catching error
5246 and issuing diagnostics are caller's responsibility. */
5247
5248static tree
5249lookup_type_scope_1 (tree name, tag_scope scope)
5250{
5251 cxx_binding *iter = NULL;
5252 tree val = NULL_TREE;
5253
5254 /* Look in non-namespace scope first. */
5255 if (current_binding_level->kind != sk_namespace)
5256 iter = outer_binding (name, NULL, /*class_p=*/ true);
5257 for (; iter; iter = outer_binding (name, iter, /*class_p=*/ true))
5258 {
5259 /* Check if this is the kind of thing we're looking for.
5260 If SCOPE is TS_CURRENT, also make sure it doesn't come from
5261 base class. For ITER->VALUE, we can simply use
5262 INHERITED_VALUE_BINDING_P. For ITER->TYPE, we have to use
5263 our own check.
5264
5265 We check ITER->TYPE before ITER->VALUE in order to handle
5266 typedef struct C {} C;
5267 correctly. */
5268
5269 if (qualify_lookup (iter->type, LOOKUP_PREFER_TYPES)
5270 && (scope != ts_current
5271 || LOCAL_BINDING_P (iter)
5272 || DECL_CONTEXT (iter->type) == iter->scope->this_entity))
5273 val = iter->type;
5274 else if ((scope != ts_current
5275 || !INHERITED_VALUE_BINDING_P (iter))
5276 && qualify_lookup (iter->value, LOOKUP_PREFER_TYPES))
5277 val = iter->value;
5278
5279 if (val)
5280 break;
5281 }
5282
5283 /* Look in namespace scope. */
5284 if (!val)
5285 {
5286 iter = cp_binding_level_find_binding_for_name
5287 (NAMESPACE_LEVEL (current_decl_namespace ()), name);
5288
5289 if (iter)
5290 {
5291 /* If this is the kind of thing we're looking for, we're done. */
5292 if (qualify_lookup (iter->type, LOOKUP_PREFER_TYPES))
5293 val = iter->type;
5294 else if (qualify_lookup (iter->value, LOOKUP_PREFER_TYPES))
5295 val = iter->value;
5296 }
5297
5298 }
5299
5300 /* Type found, check if it is in the allowed scopes, ignoring cleanup
5301 and template parameter scopes. */
5302 if (val)
5303 {
5304 cp_binding_level *b = current_binding_level;
5305 while (b)
5306 {
5307 if (iter->scope == b)
5308 return val;
5309
5310 if (b->kind == sk_cleanup || b->kind == sk_template_parms
5311 || b->kind == sk_function_parms)
5312 b = b->level_chain;
5313 else if (b->kind == sk_class
5314 && scope == ts_within_enclosing_non_class)
5315 b = b->level_chain;
5316 else
5317 break;
5318 }
5319 }
5320
5321 return NULL_TREE;
5322}

5391/* Returns true iff DECL is a block-scope extern declaration of a function
5392 or variable. */
5393
5394bool
5395is_local_extern (tree decl)
5396{
5397 cxx_binding *binding;
5398
5399 /* For functions, this is easy. */
5400 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
5401 return DECL_LOCAL_FUNCTION_P (decl);
5402
5403 if (!VAR_P (decl))
5404 return false;
5405 if (!current_function_decl)
5406 return false;
5407
5408 /* For variables, this is not easy. We need to look at the binding stack
5409 for the identifier to see whether the decl we have is a local. */
5410 for (binding = IDENTIFIER_BINDING (DECL_NAME (decl));
5411 binding && binding->scope->kind != sk_namespace;
5412 binding = binding->previous)
5413 if (binding->value == decl)
5414 return LOCAL_BINDING_P (binding);
5415
5416 return false;
5417}

5451/* [basic.lookup.koenig] */
5452/* A nonzero return value in the functions below indicates an error. */
5453
5454struct arg_lookup
5455{

5457 vec<tree, va_gc> *args;

5459 vec<tree, va_gc> *classes;

5462};
5463
5464static bool arg_assoc (struct arg_lookup*, tree);
5465static bool arg_assoc_args (struct arg_lookup*, tree);
5466static bool arg_assoc_args_vec (struct arg_lookup*, vec<tree, va_gc> *);
5467static bool arg_assoc_type (struct arg_lookup*, tree);
5468static bool add_function (struct arg_lookup *, tree);
5469static bool arg_assoc_namespace (struct arg_lookup *, tree);
5470static bool arg_assoc_class_only (struct arg_lookup *, tree);
5471static bool arg_assoc_bases (struct arg_lookup *, tree);
5472static bool arg_assoc_class (struct arg_lookup *, tree);
5473static bool arg_assoc_template_arg (struct arg_lookup*, tree);
