5475/* Add a function to the lookup structure.
5476 Returns true on error. */
5477
5478static bool
5479add_function (struct arg_lookup *k, tree fn)
5480{
5481 if (!is_overloaded_fn (fn))
5482 /* All names except those of (possibly overloaded) functions and
5483 function templates are ignored. */;
5484 else if (k->fn_set && k->fn_set->add (fn))
5485 /* It's already in the list. */;
5486 else if (!k->functions && TREE_CODE (fn) != TEMPLATE_DECL)
5487 k->functions = fn;
5488 else if (fn == k->functions)
5489 ;
5490 else
5491 {
5492 k->functions = build_overload (fn, k->functions);
5493 if (TREE_CODE (k->functions) == OVERLOAD)
5494 OVL_ARG_DEPENDENT (k->functions) = true;
5495 }
5496
5497 return false;
5498}
5499
5500/* Returns true iff CURRENT has declared itself to be an associated
5501 namespace of SCOPE via a strong using-directive (or transitive chain
5502 thereof). Both are namespaces. */
5503
5504bool
5505is_associated_namespace (tree current, tree scope)
5506{
5507 vec<tree, va_gc> *seen = make_tree_vector ();
5508 vec<tree, va_gc> *todo = make_tree_vector ();
5509 tree t;
5510 bool ret;
5511
5512 while (1)
5513 {
5514 if (scope == current)
5515 {
5516 ret = true;
5517 break;
5518 }
5519 vec_safe_push (seen, scope);
5520 for (t = DECL_NAMESPACE_ASSOCIATIONS (scope); t; t = TREE_CHAIN (t))
5521 if (!vec_member (TREE_PURPOSE (t), seen))
5522 vec_safe_push (todo, TREE_PURPOSE (t));
5523 if (!todo->is_empty ())
5524 {
5525 scope = todo->last ();
5526 todo->pop ();
5527 }
5528 else
5529 {
5530 ret = false;
5531 break;
5532 }
5533 }
5534
5535 release_tree_vector (seen);
5536 release_tree_vector (todo);
5537
5538 return ret;
5539}
5540
5541/* Add functions of a namespace to the lookup structure.
5542 Returns true on error. */
5543
5544static bool
5545arg_assoc_namespace (struct arg_lookup *k, tree scope)
5546{
5547 tree value;
5548
5549 if (vec_member (scope, k->namespaces))
5550 return false;
5551 vec_safe_push (k->namespaces, scope);
5552
5553 /* Check out our super-users. */
5554 for (value = DECL_NAMESPACE_ASSOCIATIONS (scope); value;
5555 value = TREE_CHAIN (value))
5556 if (arg_assoc_namespace (k, TREE_PURPOSE (value)))
5557 return true;
5558
5559 /* Also look down into inline namespaces. */
5560 for (value = DECL_NAMESPACE_USING (scope); value;
5561 value = TREE_CHAIN (value))
5562 if (is_associated_namespace (scope, TREE_PURPOSE (value)))
5563 if (arg_assoc_namespace (k, TREE_PURPOSE (value)))
5564 return true;
5565
5566 value = namespace_binding (k->name, scope);
5567 if (!value)
5568 return false;
5569
5570 for (; value; value = OVL_NEXT (value))
5571 {
5572 /* We don't want to find arbitrary hidden functions via argument
5573 dependent lookup. We only want to find friends of associated
5574 classes, which we'll do via arg_assoc_class. */
5575 if (hidden_name_p (OVL_CURRENT (value)))
5576 continue;
5577
5578 if (add_function (k, OVL_CURRENT (value)))
5579 return true;
5580 }
5581
5582 return false;
5583}
5584
5585/* Adds everything associated with a template argument to the lookup
5586 structure. Returns true on error. */
5587
5588static bool
5589arg_assoc_template_arg (struct arg_lookup *k, tree arg)
5590{
5591 /* [basic.lookup.koenig]
5592
5593 If T is a template-id, its associated namespaces and classes are
5594 ... the namespaces and classes associated with the types of the
5595 template arguments provided for template type parameters
5596 (excluding template template parameters); the namespaces in which
5597 any template template arguments are defined; and the classes in
5598 which any member templates used as template template arguments
5599 are defined. [Note: non-type template arguments do not
5600 contribute to the set of associated namespaces. ] */
5601
5602 /* Consider first template template arguments. */
5603 if (TREE_CODE (arg) == TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM
5604 || TREE_CODE (arg) == UNBOUND_CLASS_TEMPLATE)
5605 return false;
5606 else if (TREE_CODE (arg) == TEMPLATE_DECL)
5607 {
5608 tree ctx = CP_DECL_CONTEXT (arg);
5609
5610 /* It's not a member template. */
5611 if (TREE_CODE (ctx) == NAMESPACE_DECL)
5612 return arg_assoc_namespace (k, ctx);
5613 /* Otherwise, it must be member template. */
5614 else
5615 return arg_assoc_class_only (k, ctx);
5616 }
5617 /* It's an argument pack; handle it recursively. */
5618 else if (ARGUMENT_PACK_P (arg))
5619 {
5620 tree args = ARGUMENT_PACK_ARGS (arg);
5621 int i, len = TREE_VEC_LENGTH (args);
5622 for (i = 0; i < len; ++i)
5623 if (arg_assoc_template_arg (k, TREE_VEC_ELT (args, i)))
5624 return true;
5625
5626 return false;
5627 }
5628 /* It's not a template template argument, but it is a type template
5629 argument. */
5630 else if (TYPE_P (arg))
5631 return arg_assoc_type (k, arg);
5632 /* It's a non-type template argument. */
5633 else
5634 return false;
5635}
5636
5637/* Adds the class and its friends to the lookup structure.
5638 Returns true on error. */
5639
5640static bool
5641arg_assoc_class_only (struct arg_lookup *k, tree type)
5642{
5643 tree list, friends, context;
5644
5645 /* Backend-built structures, such as __builtin_va_list, aren't
5646 affected by all this. */
5647 if (!CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
5648 return false;
5649
5650 context = decl_namespace_context (type);
5651 if (arg_assoc_namespace (k, context))
5652 return true;
5653
5654 complete_type (type);
5655
5656 /* Process friends. */
5657 for (list = DECL_FRIENDLIST (TYPE_MAIN_DECL (type)); list;
5658 list = TREE_CHAIN (list))
5659 if (k->name == FRIEND_NAME (list))
5660 for (friends = FRIEND_DECLS (list); friends;
5661 friends = TREE_CHAIN (friends))
5662 {
5663 tree fn = TREE_VALUE (friends);
5664
5665 /* Only interested in global functions with potentially hidden
5666 (i.e. unqualified) declarations. */
5667 if (CP_DECL_CONTEXT (fn) != context)
5668 continue;
5669 /* Template specializations are never found by name lookup.
5670 (Templates themselves can be found, but not template
5671 specializations.) */
5672 if (TREE_CODE (fn) == FUNCTION_DECL && DECL_USE_TEMPLATE (fn))
5673 continue;
5674 if (add_function (k, fn))
5675 return true;
5676 }
5677
5678 return false;
5679}
5680
5681/* Adds the class and its bases to the lookup structure.
5682 Returns true on error. */
5683
5684static bool
5685arg_assoc_bases (struct arg_lookup *k, tree type)
5686{
5687 if (arg_assoc_class_only (k, type))
5688 return true;
5689
5690 if (TYPE_BINFO (type))
5691 {
5692 /* Process baseclasses. */
5693 tree binfo, base_binfo;
5694 int i;
5695
5696 for (binfo = TYPE_BINFO (type), i = 0;
5697 BINFO_BASE_ITERATE (binfo, i, base_binfo); i++)
5698 if (arg_assoc_bases (k, BINFO_TYPE (base_binfo)))
5699 return true;
5700 }
5701
5702 return false;
5703}
5704
5705/* Adds everything associated with a class argument type to the lookup
5706 structure. Returns true on error.
5707
5708 If T is a class type (including unions), its associated classes are: the
5709 class itself; the class of which it is a member, if any; and its direct
5710 and indirect base classes. Its associated namespaces are the namespaces
5711 of which its associated classes are members. Furthermore, if T is a
5712 class template specialization, its associated namespaces and classes
5713 also include: the namespaces and classes associated with the types of
5714 the template arguments provided for template type parameters (excluding
5715 template template parameters); the namespaces of which any template
5716 template arguments are members; and the classes of which any member
5717 templates used as template template arguments are members. [ Note:
5718 non-type template arguments do not contribute to the set of associated
5719 namespaces. --end note] */
5720
5721static bool
5722arg_assoc_class (struct arg_lookup *k, tree type)
5723{
5724 tree list;
5725 int i;
5726
5727 /* Backend build structures, such as __builtin_va_list, aren't
5728 affected by all this. */
5729 if (!CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
5730 return false;
5731
5732 if (vec_member (type, k->classes))
5733 return false;
5734 vec_safe_push (k->classes, type);
5735
5736 if (TYPE_CLASS_SCOPE_P (type)
5737 && arg_assoc_class_only (k, TYPE_CONTEXT (type)))
5738 return true;
5739
5740 if (arg_assoc_bases (k, type))
5741 return true;
5742
5743 /* Process template arguments. */
5744 if (CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (type)
5745 && PRIMARY_TEMPLATE_P (CLASSTYPE_TI_TEMPLATE (type)))
5746 {
5747 list = INNERMOST_TEMPLATE_ARGS (CLASSTYPE_TI_ARGS (type));
5748 for (i = 0; i < TREE_VEC_LENGTH (list); ++i)
5749 if (arg_assoc_template_arg (k, TREE_VEC_ELT (list, i)))
5750 return true;
5751 }
5752
5753 return false;
5754}
5755
5756/* Adds everything associated with a given type.
5757 Returns 1 on error. */
5758
5759static bool
5760arg_assoc_type (struct arg_lookup *k, tree type)
5761{
5762 /* As we do not get the type of non-type dependent expressions
5763 right, we can end up with such things without a type. */
5764 if (!type)
5765 return false;
5766
5767 if (TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (type))
5768 {
5769 /* Pointer to member: associate class type and value type. */
5770 if (arg_assoc_type (k, TYPE_PTRMEM_CLASS_TYPE (type)))
5771 return true;
5772 return arg_assoc_type (k, TYPE_PTRMEM_POINTED_TO_TYPE (type));
5773 }
5774 else switch (TREE_CODE (type))
5775 {
5776 case ERROR_MARK:
5777 return false;
5778 case VOID_TYPE:
5779 case INTEGER_TYPE:
5780 case REAL_TYPE:
5781 case COMPLEX_TYPE:
5782 case VECTOR_TYPE:
5783 case BOOLEAN_TYPE:
5784 case FIXED_POINT_TYPE:
5785 case DECLTYPE_TYPE:
5786 case NULLPTR_TYPE:
5787 return false;
5788 case RECORD_TYPE:
5789 if (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (type))
5790 return arg_assoc_type (k, TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_FN_TYPE (type));
5791 /* FALLTHRU */
5792 case UNION_TYPE:
5793 return arg_assoc_class (k, type);
5794 case POINTER_TYPE:
5795 case REFERENCE_TYPE:
5796 case ARRAY_TYPE:
5797 return arg_assoc_type (k, TREE_TYPE (type));
5798 case ENUMERAL_TYPE:
5799 if (TYPE_CLASS_SCOPE_P (type)
5800 && arg_assoc_class_only (k, TYPE_CONTEXT (type)))
5801 return true;
5802 return arg_assoc_namespace (k, decl_namespace_context (type));
5803 case METHOD_TYPE:
5804 /* The basetype is referenced in the first arg type, so just
5805 fall through. */
5806 case FUNCTION_TYPE:
5807 /* Associate the parameter types. */
5808 if (arg_assoc_args (k, TYPE_ARG_TYPES (type)))
5809 return true;
5810 /* Associate the return type. */
5811 return arg_assoc_type (k, TREE_TYPE (type));
5812 case TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM:
5813 case BOUND_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM:
5814 return false;
5815 case TYPENAME_TYPE:
5816 return false;
5817 case LANG_TYPE:
5818 gcc_assert (type == unknown_type_node
5819 || type == init_list_type_node);
5820 return false;
5821 case TYPE_PACK_EXPANSION:
5822 return arg_assoc_type (k, PACK_EXPANSION_PATTERN (type));
5823
5824 default:
5825 gcc_unreachable ();
5826 }
5827 return false;
5828}
5829
5830/* Adds everything associated with arguments. Returns true on error. */
5831
5832static bool
5833arg_assoc_args (struct arg_lookup *k, tree args)
5834{
5835 for (; args; args = TREE_CHAIN (args))
5836 if (arg_assoc (k, TREE_VALUE (args)))
5837 return true;
5838 return false;
5839}
5840
5841/* Adds everything associated with an argument vector. Returns true
5842 on error. */
5843
5844static bool
5845arg_assoc_args_vec (struct arg_lookup *k, vec<tree, va_gc> *args)
5846{
5847 unsigned int ix;
5848 tree arg;
5849
5850 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (args, ix, arg)
5851 if (arg_assoc (k, arg))
5852 return true;
5853 return false;
5854}
5855
5856/* Adds everything associated with a given tree_node. Returns 1 on error. */
5857
5858static bool
5859arg_assoc (struct arg_lookup *k, tree n)
5860{
5861 if (n == error_mark_node)
5862 return false;
5863
5864 if (TYPE_P (n))
5865 return arg_assoc_type (k, n);
5866
5867 if (! type_unknown_p (n))
5868 return arg_assoc_type (k, TREE_TYPE (n));
5869
5870 if (TREE_CODE (n) == ADDR_EXPR)
5871 n = TREE_OPERAND (n, 0);
5872 if (TREE_CODE (n) == COMPONENT_REF)
5873 n = TREE_OPERAND (n, 1);
5874 if (TREE_CODE (n) == OFFSET_REF)
5875 n = TREE_OPERAND (n, 1);
5876 while (TREE_CODE (n) == TREE_LIST)
5877 n = TREE_VALUE (n);
5878 if (BASELINK_P (n))
5879 n = BASELINK_FUNCTIONS (n);
5880
5881 if (TREE_CODE (n) == FUNCTION_DECL)
5882 return arg_assoc_type (k, TREE_TYPE (n));
5883 if (TREE_CODE (n) == TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR)
5884 {
5885 /* The working paper doesn't currently say how to handle template-id
5886 arguments. The sensible thing would seem to be to handle the list
5887 of template candidates like a normal overload set, and handle the
5888 template arguments like we do for class template
5889 specializations. */
5890 tree templ = TREE_OPERAND (n, 0);
5891 tree args = TREE_OPERAND (n, 1);
5892 int ix;
5893
5894 /* First the templates. */
5895 if (arg_assoc (k, templ))
5896 return true;
5897
5898 /* Now the arguments. */
5899 if (args)
5900 for (ix = TREE_VEC_LENGTH (args); ix--;)
5901 if (arg_assoc_template_arg (k, TREE_VEC_ELT (args, ix)) == 1)
5902 return true;
5903 }
5904 else if (TREE_CODE (n) == OVERLOAD)
5905 {
5906 for (; n; n = OVL_NEXT (n))
5907 if (arg_assoc_type (k, TREE_TYPE (OVL_CURRENT (n))))
5908 return true;
5909 }
5910
5911 return false;
5912}
5913
5914/* Performs Koenig lookup depending on arguments, where fns
5915 are the functions found in normal lookup. */
5916
5917static cp_expr
5918lookup_arg_dependent_1 (tree name, tree fns, vec<tree, va_gc> *args)
5919{
5920 struct arg_lookup k;
5921
5922 /* Remove any hidden friend functions from the list of functions
5923 found so far. They will be added back by arg_assoc_class as
5924 appropriate. */
5925 fns = remove_hidden_names (fns);
5926
5927 k.name = name;
5928 k.args = args;
5929 k.functions = fns;
5930 k.classes = make_tree_vector ();
5931
5932 /* We previously performed an optimization here by setting
5933 NAMESPACES to the current namespace when it was safe. However, DR
5934 164 says that namespaces that were already searched in the first
5935 stage of template processing are searched again (potentially
5936 picking up later definitions) in the second stage. */
5937 k.namespaces = make_tree_vector ();
5938
5939 /* We used to allow duplicates and let joust discard them, but
5940 since the above change for DR 164 we end up with duplicates of
5941 all the functions found by unqualified lookup. So keep track
5942 of which ones we've seen. */
5943 if (fns)
5944 {
5945 tree ovl;
5946 /* We shouldn't be here if lookup found something other than
5947 namespace-scope functions. */
5948 gcc_assert (DECL_NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P (OVL_CURRENT (fns)));
5949 k.fn_set = new hash_set<tree>;
5950 for (ovl = fns; ovl; ovl = OVL_NEXT (ovl))
5951 k.fn_set->add (OVL_CURRENT (ovl));
5952 }
5953 else
5954 k.fn_set = NULL;
5955
5956 arg_assoc_args_vec (&k, args);
5957
5958 fns = k.functions;
5959
5960 if (fns
5961 && !VAR_P (fns)
5962 && !is_overloaded_fn (fns))
5963 {
5964 error ("argument dependent lookup finds %q+D", fns);
5965 error (" in call to %qD", name);
5966 fns = error_mark_node;
5967 }
5968
5969 release_tree_vector (k.classes);
5970 release_tree_vector (k.namespaces);
5971 delete k.fn_set;
5972
5973 return fns;
5974}
5975
5976/* Wrapper for lookup_arg_dependent_1. */
5977
5978cp_expr
5979lookup_arg_dependent (tree name, tree fns, vec<tree, va_gc> *args)
5980{
5981 cp_expr ret;
5982 bool subtime;
5983 subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
5984 ret = lookup_arg_dependent_1 (name, fns, args);
5985 timevar_cond_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP, subtime);
5986 return ret;
5987}

5990/* Add namespace to using_directives. Return NULL_TREE if nothing was
5991 changed (i.e. there was already a directive), or the fresh
5992 TREE_LIST otherwise. */
5993
5994static tree
5995push_using_directive_1 (tree used)
5996{
5997 tree ud = current_binding_level->using_directives;
5998 tree iter, ancestor;
5999
6000 /* Check if we already have this. */
6001 if (purpose_member (used, ud) != NULL_TREE)
6002 return NULL_TREE;
6003
6004 ancestor = namespace_ancestor (current_decl_namespace (), used);
6005 ud = current_binding_level->using_directives;
6006 ud = tree_cons (used, ancestor, ud);
6007 current_binding_level->using_directives = ud;
6008
6009 /* Recursively add all namespaces used. */
6010 for (iter = DECL_NAMESPACE_USING (used); iter; iter = TREE_CHAIN (iter))
6011 push_using_directive (TREE_PURPOSE (iter));
6012
6013 return ud;
6014}
6015
6016/* Wrapper for push_using_directive_1. */
6017
6018static tree
6019push_using_directive (tree used)
6020{
6021 tree ret;
6022 bool subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
6023 ret = push_using_directive_1 (used);
6024 timevar_cond_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP, subtime);
6025 return ret;
6026}
6027
6028/* The type TYPE is being declared. If it is a class template, or a
6029 specialization of a class template, do any processing required and
6030 perform error-checking. If IS_FRIEND is nonzero, this TYPE is
6031 being declared a friend. B is the binding level at which this TYPE
6032 should be bound.
6033
6034 Returns the TYPE_DECL for TYPE, which may have been altered by this
6035 processing. */
6036
6037static tree
6038maybe_process_template_type_declaration (tree type, int is_friend,
6039 cp_binding_level *b)
6040{
6041 tree decl = TYPE_NAME (type);
6042
6043 if (processing_template_parmlist)
6044 /* You can't declare a new template type in a template parameter
6045 list. But, you can declare a non-template type:
6046
6047 template <class A*> struct S;
6048
6049 is a forward-declaration of `A'. */
6050 ;
6051 else if (b->kind == sk_namespace
6052 && current_binding_level->kind != sk_namespace)
6053 /* If this new type is being injected into a containing scope,
6054 then it's not a template type. */
6055 ;
6056 else
6057 {
6058 gcc_assert (MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (type)
6059 || TREE_CODE (type) == ENUMERAL_TYPE);
6060
6061 if (processing_template_decl)
6062 {
6063 /* This may change after the call to
6064 push_template_decl_real, but we want the original value. */
6065 tree name = DECL_NAME (decl);
6066
6067 decl = push_template_decl_real (decl, is_friend);
6068 if (decl == error_mark_node)
6069 return error_mark_node;
6070
6071 /* If the current binding level is the binding level for the
6072 template parameters (see the comment in
6073 begin_template_parm_list) and the enclosing level is a class
6074 scope, and we're not looking at a friend, push the
6075 declaration of the member class into the class scope. In the
6076 friend case, push_template_decl will already have put the
6077 friend into global scope, if appropriate. */
6078 if (TREE_CODE (type) != ENUMERAL_TYPE
6079 && !is_friend && b->kind == sk_template_parms
6080 && b->level_chain->kind == sk_class)
6081 {
6082 finish_member_declaration (CLASSTYPE_TI_TEMPLATE (type));
6083
6084 if (!COMPLETE_TYPE_P (current_class_type))
6085 {
6086 maybe_add_class_template_decl_list (current_class_type,
6087 type, /*friend_p=*/0);
6088 /* Put this UTD in the table of UTDs for the class. */
6089 if (CLASSTYPE_NESTED_UTDS (current_class_type) == NULL)
6090 CLASSTYPE_NESTED_UTDS (current_class_type) =
6091 binding_table_new (SCOPE_DEFAULT_HT_SIZE);
6092
6093 binding_table_insert
6094 (CLASSTYPE_NESTED_UTDS (current_class_type), name, type);
6095 }
6096 }
6097 }
6098 }
6099
6100 return decl;
6101}
6102
6103/* Push a tag name NAME for struct/class/union/enum type TYPE. In case
6104 that the NAME is a class template, the tag is processed but not pushed.
6105
6106 The pushed scope depend on the SCOPE parameter:
6107 - When SCOPE is TS_CURRENT, put it into the inner-most non-sk_cleanup
6108 scope.
6109 - When SCOPE is TS_GLOBAL, put it in the inner-most non-class and
6110 non-template-parameter scope. This case is needed for forward
6111 declarations.
6112 - When SCOPE is TS_WITHIN_ENCLOSING_NON_CLASS, this is similar to
6113 TS_GLOBAL case except that names within template-parameter scopes
6114 are not pushed at all.
6115
6116 Returns TYPE upon success and ERROR_MARK_NODE otherwise. */
6117
6118static tree
6119pushtag_1 (tree name, tree type, tag_scope scope)
6120{
6121 cp_binding_level *b;
6122 tree decl;
6123
6124 b = current_binding_level;
6125 while (/* Cleanup scopes are not scopes from the point of view of
6126 the language. */
6127 b->kind == sk_cleanup
6128 /* Neither are function parameter scopes. */
6129 || b->kind == sk_function_parms
6130 /* Neither are the scopes used to hold template parameters
6131 for an explicit specialization. For an ordinary template
6132 declaration, these scopes are not scopes from the point of
6133 view of the language. */
6134 || (b->kind == sk_template_parms
6135 && (b->explicit_spec_p || scope == ts_global))
6136 || (b->kind == sk_class
6137 && (scope != ts_current
6138 /* We may be defining a new type in the initializer
6139 of a static member variable. We allow this when
6140 not pedantic, and it is particularly useful for
6141 type punning via an anonymous union. */
6142 || COMPLETE_TYPE_P (b->this_entity))))
6143 b = b->level_chain;
6144
6145 gcc_assert (identifier_p (name));
6146
6147 /* Do C++ gratuitous typedefing. */
6148 if (identifier_type_value_1 (name) != type)
6149 {
6150 tree tdef;
6151 int in_class = 0;
6152 tree context = TYPE_CONTEXT (type);
6153
6154 if (! context)
6155 {
6156 tree cs = current_scope ();
6157
6158 if (scope == ts_current
6159 || (cs && TREE_CODE (cs) == FUNCTION_DECL))
6160 context = cs;
6161 else if (cs != NULL_TREE && TYPE_P (cs))
6162 /* When declaring a friend class of a local class, we want
6163 to inject the newly named class into the scope
6164 containing the local class, not the namespace
6165 scope. */
6166 context = decl_function_context (get_type_decl (cs));
6167 }
6168 if (!context)
6169 context = current_namespace;
6170
6171 if (b->kind == sk_class
6172 || (b->kind == sk_template_parms
6173 && b->level_chain->kind == sk_class))
6174 in_class = 1;
6175
6176 tdef = create_implicit_typedef (name, type);
6177 DECL_CONTEXT (tdef) = FROB_CONTEXT (context);
6178 if (scope == ts_within_enclosing_non_class)
6179 {
6180 /* This is a friend. Make this TYPE_DECL node hidden from
6181 ordinary name lookup. Its corresponding TEMPLATE_DECL
6182 will be marked in push_template_decl_real. */
6183 retrofit_lang_decl (tdef);
6184 DECL_ANTICIPATED (tdef) = 1;
6185 DECL_FRIEND_P (tdef) = 1;
6186 }
6187
6188 decl = maybe_process_template_type_declaration
6189 (type, scope == ts_within_enclosing_non_class, b);
6190 if (decl == error_mark_node)
6191 return decl;
6192
6193 if (b->kind == sk_class)
6194 {
6195 if (!TYPE_BEING_DEFINED (current_class_type))
6196 return error_mark_node;
6197
6198 if (!PROCESSING_REAL_TEMPLATE_DECL_P ())
6199 /* Put this TYPE_DECL on the TYPE_FIELDS list for the
6200 class. But if it's a member template class, we want
6201 the TEMPLATE_DECL, not the TYPE_DECL, so this is done
6202 later. */
6203 finish_member_declaration (decl);
6204 else
6205 pushdecl_class_level (decl);
6206 }
6207 else if (b->kind != sk_template_parms)
6208 {
6209 decl = pushdecl_with_scope_1 (decl, b, /*is_friend=*/false);
6210 if (decl == error_mark_node)
6211 return decl;
6212
6213 if (DECL_CONTEXT (decl) == std_node
6214 && strcmp (TYPE_NAME_STRING (type), "initializer_list") == 0
6215 && !CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (type))
6216 {
6217 error ("declaration of std::initializer_list does not match "
6218 "#include <initializer_list>, isn't a template");
6219 return error_mark_node;
6220 }
6221 }
6222
6223 if (! in_class)
6224 set_identifier_type_value_with_scope (name, tdef, b);
6225
6226 TYPE_CONTEXT (type) = DECL_CONTEXT (decl);
6227
6228 /* If this is a local class, keep track of it. We need this
6229 information for name-mangling, and so that it is possible to
6230 find all function definitions in a translation unit in a
6231 convenient way. (It's otherwise tricky to find a member
6232 function definition it's only pointed to from within a local
6233 class.) */
6234 if (TYPE_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P (type))
6235 {
6236 if (processing_template_decl)
6237 {
6238 /* Push a DECL_EXPR so we call pushtag at the right time in
6239 template instantiation rather than in some nested context. */
6240 add_decl_expr (decl);
6241 }
6242 else
6243 vec_safe_push (local_classes, type);
6244 }
6245 }
6246 if (b->kind == sk_class
6247 && !COMPLETE_TYPE_P (current_class_type))
6248 {
6249 maybe_add_class_template_decl_list (current_class_type,
6250 type, /*friend_p=*/0);
6251
6252 if (CLASSTYPE_NESTED_UTDS (current_class_type) == NULL)
6253 CLASSTYPE_NESTED_UTDS (current_class_type)
6254 = binding_table_new (SCOPE_DEFAULT_HT_SIZE);
6255
6256 binding_table_insert
6257 (CLASSTYPE_NESTED_UTDS (current_class_type), name, type);
6258 }
6259
6260 decl = TYPE_NAME (type);
6261 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL);
6262
6263 /* Set type visibility now if this is a forward declaration. */
6264 TREE_PUBLIC (decl) = 1;
6265 determine_visibility (decl);
6266
6267 return type;
6268}
6269
6270/* Wrapper for pushtag_1. */
6271
6272tree
6273pushtag (tree name, tree type, tag_scope scope)
6274{
6275 tree ret;
6276 bool subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
6277 ret = pushtag_1 (name, type, scope);
6278 timevar_cond_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP, subtime);
6279 return ret;
6280}

6283/* Subroutines for reverting temporarily to top-level for instantiation
6284 of templates and such. We actually need to clear out the class- and
6285 local-value slots of all identifiers, so that only the global values
6286 are at all visible. Simply setting current_binding_level to the global
6287 scope isn't enough, because more binding levels may be pushed. */
6288struct saved_scope *scope_chain;
6289
6290/* Return true if ID has not already been marked. */
6291
6292static inline bool
6293store_binding_p (tree id)
6294{
6295 if (!id || !IDENTIFIER_BINDING (id))
6296 return false;
6297
6298 if (IDENTIFIER_MARKED (id))
6299 return false;
6300
6301 return true;
6302}
6303
6304/* Add an appropriate binding to *OLD_BINDINGS which needs to already
6305 have enough space reserved. */
6306
6307static void
6308store_binding (tree id, vec<cxx_saved_binding, va_gc> **old_bindings)
6309{
6310 cxx_saved_binding saved;
6311
6312 gcc_checking_assert (store_binding_p (id));
6313
6314 IDENTIFIER_MARKED (id) = 1;
6315
6316 saved.identifier = id;
6317 saved.binding = IDENTIFIER_BINDING (id);
6318 saved.real_type_value = REAL_IDENTIFIER_TYPE_VALUE (id);
6319 (*old_bindings)->quick_push (saved);
6320 IDENTIFIER_BINDING (id) = NULL;
6321}
6322
6323static void
6324store_bindings (tree names, vec<cxx_saved_binding, va_gc> **old_bindings)
6325{
6326 static vec<tree> bindings_need_stored;
6327 tree t, id;
6328 size_t i;
6329
6330 bool subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
6331 for (t = names; t; t = TREE_CHAIN (t))
6332 {
6333 if (TREE_CODE (t) == TREE_LIST)
6334 id = TREE_PURPOSE (t);
6335 else
6336 id = DECL_NAME (t);
6337
6338 if (store_binding_p (id))
6339 bindings_need_stored.safe_push (id);
6340 }
6341 if (!bindings_need_stored.is_empty ())
6342 {
6343 vec_safe_reserve_exact (*old_bindings, bindings_need_stored.length ());
6344 for (i = 0; bindings_need_stored.iterate (i, &id); ++i)
6345 {
6346 /* We can apparently have duplicates in NAMES. */
6347 if (store_binding_p (id))
6348 store_binding (id, old_bindings);
6349 }
6350 bindings_need_stored.truncate (0);
6351 }
6352 timevar_cond_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP, subtime);
6353}
6354
6355/* Like store_bindings, but NAMES is a vector of cp_class_binding
6356 objects, rather than a TREE_LIST. */
6357
6358static void
6359store_class_bindings (vec<cp_class_binding, va_gc> *names,
6360 vec<cxx_saved_binding, va_gc> **old_bindings)
6361{
6362 static vec<tree> bindings_need_stored;
6363 size_t i;
6364 cp_class_binding *cb;
6365
6366 bool subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
6367 for (i = 0; vec_safe_iterate (names, i, &cb); ++i)
6368 if (store_binding_p (cb->identifier))
6369 bindings_need_stored.safe_push (cb->identifier);
6370 if (!bindings_need_stored.is_empty ())
6371 {
6372 tree id;
6373 vec_safe_reserve_exact (*old_bindings, bindings_need_stored.length ());
6374 for (i = 0; bindings_need_stored.iterate (i, &id); ++i)
6375 store_binding (id, old_bindings);
6376 bindings_need_stored.truncate (0);
6377 }
6378 timevar_cond_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP, subtime);
6379}
6380
6381/* A chain of saved_scope structures awaiting reuse. */
6382
6383static GTY((deletable)) struct saved_scope *free_saved_scope;
6384
6385void
6386push_to_top_level (void)
6387{
6388 struct saved_scope *s;
6389 cp_binding_level *b;
6390 cxx_saved_binding *sb;
6391 size_t i;
6392 bool need_pop;
6393
6394 bool subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
6395
6396 /* Reuse or create a new structure for this saved scope. */
6397 if (free_saved_scope != NULL)
6398 {
6399 s = free_saved_scope;
6400 free_saved_scope = s->prev;
6401
6402 vec<cxx_saved_binding, va_gc> *old_bindings = s->old_bindings;
6403 memset (s, 0, sizeof (*s));
6404 /* Also reuse the structure's old_bindings vector. */
6405 vec_safe_truncate (old_bindings, 0);
6406 s->old_bindings = old_bindings;
6407 }
6408 else
6409 s = ggc_cleared_alloc<saved_scope> ();
6410
6411 b = scope_chain ? current_binding_level : 0;
6412
6413 /* If we're in the middle of some function, save our state. */
6414 if (cfun)
6415 {
6416 need_pop = true;
6417 push_function_context ();
6418 }
6419 else
6420 need_pop = false;
6421
6422 if (scope_chain && previous_class_level)
6423 store_class_bindings (previous_class_level->class_shadowed,
6424 &s->old_bindings);
6425
6426 /* Have to include the global scope, because class-scope decls
6427 aren't listed anywhere useful. */
6428 for (; b; b = b->level_chain)
6429 {
6430 tree t;
6431
6432 /* Template IDs are inserted into the global level. If they were
6433 inserted into namespace level, finish_file wouldn't find them
6434 when doing pending instantiations. Therefore, don't stop at
6435 namespace level, but continue until :: . */
6436 if (global_scope_p (b))
6437 break;
6438
6439 store_bindings (b->names, &s->old_bindings);
6440 /* We also need to check class_shadowed to save class-level type
6441 bindings, since pushclass doesn't fill in b->names. */
6442 if (b->kind == sk_class)
6443 store_class_bindings (b->class_shadowed, &s->old_bindings);
6444
6445 /* Unwind type-value slots back to top level. */
6446 for (t = b->type_shadowed; t; t = TREE_CHAIN (t))
6447 SET_IDENTIFIER_TYPE_VALUE (TREE_PURPOSE (t), TREE_VALUE (t));
6448 }
6449
6450 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (s->old_bindings, i, sb)
6451 IDENTIFIER_MARKED (sb->identifier) = 0;
6452
6453 s->prev = scope_chain;
6454 s->bindings = b;
6455 s->need_pop_function_context = need_pop;
6456 s->function_decl = current_function_decl;
6457 s->unevaluated_operand = cp_unevaluated_operand;
6458 s->inhibit_evaluation_warnings = c_inhibit_evaluation_warnings;
6459 s->x_stmt_tree.stmts_are_full_exprs_p = true;
6460
6461 scope_chain = s;
6462 current_function_decl = NULL_TREE;
6463 vec_alloc (current_lang_base, 10);
6464 current_lang_name = lang_name_cplusplus;
6465 current_namespace = global_namespace;
6466 push_class_stack ();
6467 cp_unevaluated_operand = 0;
6468 c_inhibit_evaluation_warnings = 0;
6469 timevar_cond_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP, subtime);
6470}
6471
6472static void
6473pop_from_top_level_1 (void)
6474{
6475 struct saved_scope *s = scope_chain;
6476 cxx_saved_binding *saved;
6477 size_t i;
6478
6479 /* Clear out class-level bindings cache. */
6480 if (previous_class_level)
6481 invalidate_class_lookup_cache ();
6482 pop_class_stack ();
6483
6484 current_lang_base = 0;
6485
6486 scope_chain = s->prev;
6487 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (s->old_bindings, i, saved)
6488 {
6489 tree id = saved->identifier;
6490
6491 IDENTIFIER_BINDING (id) = saved->binding;
6492 SET_IDENTIFIER_TYPE_VALUE (id, saved->real_type_value);
6493 }
6494
6495 /* If we were in the middle of compiling a function, restore our
6496 state. */
6497 if (s->need_pop_function_context)
6498 pop_function_context ();
6499 current_function_decl = s->function_decl;
6500 cp_unevaluated_operand = s->unevaluated_operand;
6501 c_inhibit_evaluation_warnings = s->inhibit_evaluation_warnings;
6502
6503 /* Make this saved_scope structure available for reuse by
6504 push_to_top_level. */
6505 s->prev = free_saved_scope;
6506 free_saved_scope = s;
6507}
6508
6509/* Wrapper for pop_from_top_level_1. */
6510
6511void
6512pop_from_top_level (void)
6513{
6514 bool subtime = timevar_cond_start (TV_NAME_LOOKUP);
6515 pop_from_top_level_1 ();
6516 timevar_cond_stop (TV_NAME_LOOKUP, subtime);
6517}

6520/* Pop off extraneous binding levels left over due to syntax errors.
6521
6522 We don't pop past namespaces, as they might be valid. */
6523
6524void
6525pop_everything (void)
6526{
6527 if (ENABLE_SCOPE_CHECKING)
6528 verbatim ("XXX entering pop_everything ()\n");
6529 while (!toplevel_bindings_p ())
6530 {
6531 if (current_binding_level->kind == sk_class)
6532 pop_nested_class ();
6533 else
6534 poplevel (0, 0, 0);
6535 }
6536 if (ENABLE_SCOPE_CHECKING)
6537 verbatim ("XXX leaving pop_everything ()\n");
6538}

6540/* Emit debugging information for using declarations and directives.
6541 If input tree is overloaded fn then emit debug info for all
6542 candidates. */
6543
6544void
6545cp_emit_debug_info_for_using (tree t, tree context)
6546{
6547 /* Don't try to emit any debug information if we have errors. */
6548 if (seen_error ())
6549 return;
6550
6551 /* Ignore this FUNCTION_DECL if it refers to a builtin declaration
6552 of a builtin function. */
6553 if (TREE_CODE (t) == FUNCTION_DECL
6554 && DECL_EXTERNAL (t)
6555 && DECL_BUILT_IN (t))
6556 return;
6557
6558 /* Do not supply context to imported_module_or_decl, if
6559 it is a global namespace. */
6560 if (context == global_namespace)
6561 context = NULL_TREE;
6562
6563 if (BASELINK_P (t))
6564 t = BASELINK_FUNCTIONS (t);
6565
6566 /* FIXME: Handle TEMPLATE_DECLs. */
6567 for (t = OVL_CURRENT (t); t; t = OVL_NEXT (t))
6568 if (TREE_CODE (t) != TEMPLATE_DECL)
6569 {
6570 if (building_stmt_list_p ())
6571 add_stmt (build_stmt (input_location, USING_STMT, t));
6572 else
6573 (*debug_hooks->imported_module_or_decl) (t, NULL_TREE, context, false);
6574 }
6575}
